d end to end against the current sk-doc templates or HVR voice standards. The README was undersized at 174 LOC with only 6 of the 9 sections that the system-spec-kit README structural anchor prescribes. The SKILL.md frontmatter description was 240 chars (over the 130-char skill limit). Two artifacts (SKILL.md and README.md) carried a broken changelog path reference (`v1.0.0.md` instead of `v1.0.0.0.md`). A top-level `## Council Primitives` H2 inside section 3 broke the numbered-H2-ALL-CAPS rule.\n\n  Line 19: The README was rewritten from 174 LOC to 470 LOC. The new structure follows the system-spec-kit 9-section pattern (OVERVIEW, QUICK START, FEATURES with 7 sub-domains, STRUCTURE, CONFIGURATION, USAGE EXAMPLES, TROUBLESHOOTING, FAQ, RELATED DOCUMENTS). The voice is anchored at ~70% of `Public/README.md` intensity. HVR self-scoring caught zero em dashes, zero prose semicolons, zero banned metaphors, zero setup-language patterns and zero copula-avoidance constructions. `validate_document.py --type readme` exits 0.\n\n  Line 63: No consumer action required. The script-interface contract (argv shape, stdout JSON shape, exit codes) is unchanged. TS import paths into `lib/` are unchanged. The SQLite schema is unchanged at version 2. `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` glob still picks up tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/`.\n\n  Line 78: - **Structural anchor**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md` (9-section pattern)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/artifact-dir-override-parity.md:\n  Line 16: that the `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir` override correctly bypasses `resolveArtifactRoot`\n\n  Line 31: - Expected signals: `if_absent.command` = original `node -e \"...resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', '...')...\"` byte-for-byte; `step_fanout_spawn` has `skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"`; `step_fanout_merge` has `skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"`; full vitest suite passes.\n\n  Line 46: 2. Confirm `if_absent.command` contains `resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')` — byte-identical to pre-change.\n\n  Line 50: 6. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/`\n\n  Line 59: - `if_absent` branch modified: `resolveArtifactRoot` receives wrong arguments, breaking artifact dir resolution for all single-executor runs.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/check-contract-drift.cjs:\n  Line 39:   '.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.3.0.0.md:\n  Line 11: 1. The runtime SQLite directory was named `storage/` while the sibling `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` uses `database/`. The inconsistent name made the convention harder to follow and the sqlite inside was committed to git, so external repo users shipped a stale binary database instead of regenerating a fresh one on first run.\n\n  Line 64: - **Convention precedent**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-run-cli-lineage-spawn.md:\n  Line 47: 3. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:\n  Line 14:   autoModeContract: '.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md',\n\n  Line 491:         'classifierPath: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/gate-3-classifier.ts',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:\n  Line 1: This is the first shipped release of `deep-loop-runtime`. The earlier `v0.1.0` state was a phase-001 scaffold. Version `1.0.0` marks the runtime as populated and verified: shared deep-loop libraries, coverage-graph ownership, direct script entry points, SQLite storage, and runtime tests now live together in the peer skill instead of inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`.\n\n  Line 9: Before 118, every change to the deep-review or deep-research loop infrastructure required touching files inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`. Two consumer skills (`deep-review`, `deep-research`) depended on internals of a third skill (`system-spec-kit`), and the MCP tool surface (`mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*`) added a marshalling layer between workflow YAMLs and the SQLite-backed coverage graph. The arrangement was accumulated drift from early MCP server scaffolding; no ADR justified it. Arc 118 (FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP, user-directive override of the 117 AI Council SPLIT ruling) consolidated all deep-loop runtime infrastructure into this peer skill, removed the MCP tool surface entirely, and replaced it with direct `.cjs` script invocation — the same pattern `reduce-state.cjs` already used. Workflow YAML calls became one-step (`bash: node .../scripts/<name>.cjs`) instead of two-step (MCP-dispatch then JSON-parse).\n\n  Line 43: - The `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` for cross-package test discovery, so a single `pnpm vitest run` exercises both surfaces.\n\n  Line 59: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/` | 10 shared runtime modules moved from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/`. |\n\n  Line 60: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/` | 3 coverage-graph modules moved from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/`. |\n\n  Line 72: Consumers should call the four `.cjs` scripts directly rather than attempting to use the deleted `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` MCP tools. The migration source was `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`; after arc 118, the runtime owner is `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`. Workflow YAMLs (`spec_kit_deep-{review,research}_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) were updated to invoke the scripts via `bash:` blocks; `/doctor` diagnostics and the `system-code-graph` playbook scenario 009 were updated correspondingly. The `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` glob was extended to discover tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-merge-research.md:\n  Line 45: 2. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:\n  Line 31: Two new unit test files for the previously-uncovered `coverage-graph-query` (8 tests) and `coverage-graph-signals` (9 tests). Two weak council tests deepened: multi-seat-dispatch (2 to 6 tests) and round-state-jsonl (2 to 6 tests). All 29 tests pass via the system-spec-kit vitest harness.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-config-schema.md:\n  Line 40: - vitest resolves from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`.\n\n  Line 45: 2. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-config.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-salvage-recovery.md:\n  Line 48: 3. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-salvage.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-merge-review-strongest-restriction.md:\n  Line 45: 2. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts --reporter=verbose`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:\n  Line 38: Several deep loops shared the same runtime code. Each needed executor config parsing. Each needed atomic state-log writes and single-writer locking. Each needed a coverage graph that survives a session crash. Each needed Bayesian convergence scoring. Before this skill existed, all of that lived inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` and got reached through MCP tools. The consumer modes depended on the internals of a separate package, every workflow call paid the MCP marshalling and JSON-parse round-trip, and each loop would otherwise duplicate executor config, atomic-state writes, JSONL repair, single-writer locking, coverage-graph ownership, Bayesian scoring and fallback routing.\n\n  Line 44: `deep-loop-runtime` provides three component families through TypeScript imports under `lib/` and `.cjs` script entry points under `scripts/`, plus shared lifecycle, observability, and test-harness helpers surfaced in the catalog. The deep-loop family owns executor config, prompt-pack rendering, post-dispatch validation, atomic state, JSONL repair, loop locking, permissions gating, Bayesian scoring and fallback routing. It also hosts the shared backend contracts the consumer modes ride: a parameterized capability resolver, the artifact-topology seam (`resolveArtifactRoot`), the terminal lifecycle taxonomy (seven `stopReason` plus four `sessionOutcome` values) and a CLI adapter over the loop lock. The coverage-graph family owns the SQLite schema, query builders and convergence-signal extraction. The council family owns multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator-verdict scoring, cost guards, session-state hierarchy and the council graph. The workflow modes import what they need. No mode invokes this skill directly, and none of these contracts register an MCP tool. It is the foundation they ride.\n\n  Line 81: pnpm --dir .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server exec vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests\n\n  Line 84: Expected output: the vitest runner discovers the unit, integration and lifecycle tests through the cross-package glob in `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts`. A green run confirms the runtime is wired correctly.\n\n  Line 127: `system-spec-kit` owns the spec folder, validation and memory continuity. `sk-code` owns code standards and test verification. This runtime owns the infrastructure the loops ride and nothing else.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:\n  Line 1011:     `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override — do NOT run the resolveArtifactRoot node`,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:\n  Line 11:     \"typecheck\": \"../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc --noEmit --composite false -p tsconfig.json\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/README.md:\n  Line 12: vitest harnesses validating runtime primitives. Run via the system-spec-kit vitest config.\n\n  Line 31: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server\n\n  Line 39: - vitest config: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md:\n  Line 96: The runtime tests are discovered from the system-spec-kit MCP server Vitest config:\n\n  Line 99: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts\n\n  Line 106: - `coverage-graph-db.ts`, `coverage-graph-signals.ts`, and `council/council-graph-db.ts` import `better-sqlite3` (declared here; pinned to the same version `system-spec-kit` uses so the native binding stays ABI-compatible).\n\n  Line 109: The dependency versions are kept in lockstep with `system-spec-kit` (see `package.json`), which is why graph metadata still lists `system-spec-kit` under `depends_on`. The standalone suite runs via `npm test` (local `vitest.config.ts`); the combined CI run still discovers these tests through the `system-spec-kit` MCP server config above.\n\n  Line 169: | 6 | Legacy MCP server READMEs | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/README.md:25-68` + `.../handlers/coverage-graph/README.md` | Original-location stubs documenting the runtime move |\n\n  Line 174: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/deep-loop/review-depth-reducer.vitest.ts:9` imports `'../../../../deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs'` - the test file lives in `mcp_server` but exercises `deep-review` code, and is discovered via deep-loop-runtime's vitest glob in `vitest.config.ts:20`. Effective SC-007 boundary for any deep-loop-runtime change is therefore tighter than the literal directory listing: changes to `deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` ALSO re-validate through deep-loop-runtime's test surface.\n\n  Line 202: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` | Runtime test discovery. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/script_interface_contract.md:\n  Line 41: - Scripts resolve `system-spec-kit/scripts/node_modules/tsx/dist/loader.mjs`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/README.md:\n  Line 66: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-value-scenarios.vitest.ts\n\n  Line 75:   npm run --prefix .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server test:council\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/data/README.md:\n  Line 55: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-value-scenarios.vitest.ts\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/dependency-seams.vitest.ts:\n  Line 7: // system-spec-kit's internal layout and risks a native-binding ABI mismatch.\n\n  Line 24: // Versions system-spec-kit pins. The runtime must install the SAME versions so a\n\n  Line 47:     const siblingNodeModules = resolve(skillsRoot, 'system-spec-kit') + sep;\n\n  Line 54:   it('installs the same dependency versions system-spec-kit pins', () => {\n\n  Line 71:     const REACH_IN = /system-spec-kit[\\\\/](?:mcp_server|scripts)[\\\\/]node_modules/;\n\n  Line 72:     const REACH_IN_ARRAY = /'system-spec-kit'\\s*,\\s*'(?:mcp_server|scripts)'\\s*,\\s*'node_modules'/;\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/optimizer-manifest-anti-convergence.vitest.ts:\n  Line 54:   'system-spec-kit',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/README.md:\n  Line 12: Isolated per-module regression coverage for runtime libraries under `lib/deep-loop/`, `lib/coverage-graph/`, council graph queries, CLI guardrails, fan-out helpers, lifecycle taxonomy, host-driven improvement, and related runtime contracts. Each file targets one module or contract surface with no end-to-end script orchestration. Discovered by the system-spec-kit MCP server vitest config glob.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/