{"type":"text","timestamp":1783487500796,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"id":"prt_f402370a30016KQBGC8FwxoyHs","messageID":"msg_f4023662b001xZO04xMis3mrhL","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","type":"text","text":"There is already a typed `fallback-router.ts`, but the active model registry keeps `fallback_target: null` for both GLM and MiMo and explicitly documents manual reroute only. Next I’m checking whether any caller actually imports or invokes the router.","time":{"start":1783487492259,"end":1783487500794},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0002b5d0c35abf11016a4ddc0445b08191b875a6ea5fdd869e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487500856,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_PBd3cRqVx9tAOWb8jJ6xDlHZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"fallback-router|createFallbackRouter|validateFallbackGraph|resolveFallback","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime","include":"*.{ts,cjs,js,md}"},"output":"Found 71 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:\n  Line 31: | `fallback-router.ts` | Executor fallback routing. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:\n  Line 299: export function validateFallbackGraph(\n\n  Line 320: export function createFallbackRouter(\n\n  Line 324:   validateFallbackGraph(registry, options);\n\n  Line 332:       return resolveFallback(failedModelId, registry, approvedModelIds, context);\n\n  Line 357: export function resolveFallback(\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:\n  Line 206: - `fallback-router.ts` — executor fallback decision matrix\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 147: > **Feature File:** [DLR-003](01--executor/fallback-router.md)\n\n  Line 162: > **Feature File:** [DLR-044](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md)\n\n  Line 852: | Executor | `tests/unit/executor-config.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/executor-audit*.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/cli-matrix.vitest.ts` | Executor parsing, audit, fallback, and CLI dispatch behavior. |\n\n  Line 871: | DLR-003 | [F003 Fallback router](../feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md) | [01--executor/fallback-router.md](01--executor/fallback-router.md) |\n\n  Line 912: | DLR-044 | [F042 Fallback-router typed reroute](../feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) | [01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:\n  Line 92: `lib/deep-loop/` holds the loop infrastructure. `executor-config` parses per-iteration executor settings from a shared schema so every consumer calls the same executor shape. `executor-audit` appends a provenance block to each iteration JSONL so you can tell which model and CLI produced each iteration. `prompt-pack` renders the iteration prompt template. `post-dispatch-validate` checks that an iteration produced valid markdown, JSONL and delta outputs before the state log accepts them, stamps seekable log-region offsets, and quarantines failed LLM-judge fallback cards. `atomic-state` writes state logs through a tmpfile-plus-rename pattern, adds compare-before-write, SHA-256 integrity helpers, and a deferred writer, so a crash never leaves a partial line and unchanged snapshots can avoid redundant writes. `jsonl-repair` recovers a corrupt trailing line before append and supports lock-held fan-out salvage merges. `loop-lock` enforces single-writer access around state mutations, with heartbeat metadata and opt-in host-local single-flight acquisition. `permissions-gate` checks permission scope before touching sensitive paths. `bayesian-scorer` exports the small Bayesian helpers `computeScore` and `shouldDemote`; `convergence.cjs` builds the typed loop decisions. `fallback-router` picks a replacement executor when the primary one times out and validates typed reroute graphs before dispatch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:\n  Line 25: - 3.3 Scoring and routing (2 modules: bayesian-scorer, 