tIso,\n393:       completed_at_iso: completedAtIso,\n394:       duration_ms: durationMs,\n395:       error: normalizedError,\n396:     };\n397:   }\n398: }\n399: \n400: /**\n401:  * Run items through a worker with at most `concurrency` in flight.\n402:  *\n403:  * This is the fan-out generalization of council `dispatchCouncilSeats`: same\n404:  * never-throws per-item settlement and ordered results, plus a concurrency cap\n405:  * so a large lineage set runs K-at-a-time (the proven `xargs -P K` shape).\n406:  *\n407:  * @param {Object} options - Pool configuration.\n408:  * @param {Array} options.items - Work items (each ideally has a `label`).\n409:  * @param {number} options.concurrency - Max items in flight (clamped to >= 1).\n410:  * @param {Function} options.worker - Async worker: (item, { index, signal? }) => output.\n411:  * @param {Function} [options.now] - Callable returning a Date/ISO timestamp.\n412:  * @param {Function} [options.onEvent] - Optional ledger-event callback.\n413:  * @param {string} [options.lagCeilingAction] - Optional `abort-requeue` action.\n414:  * @returns {Promise<Object>} { results: [...ordered], summary: { total,\n415:  *   succeeded, failed, all_failed } }.\n416:  * @throws {TypeError} If items is not an array or worker is not a function.\n417:  */\n418: function runCappedPool(options) {\n419:   if (!isRecord(options)) {\n420:     throw new TypeError('runCappedPool options must be an object');\n421:   }\n422:   const { items, worker } = options;\n423:   if (!Array.isArray(items)) {\n424:     throw new TypeError('items must be an array');\n425:   }\n426:   if (typeof worker !== 'function') {\n427:     throw new TypeError('worker must be a function');\n428:   }\n429: \n430:   const concurrency = normalizeConcurrency(options.concurrency);\n431:   const now = typeof options.now === 'function' ? options.now : () => new Date();\n432:   const onEvent = typeof options.onEvent === 'function' ? options.onEvent : undefined;\n433:   const maxRetries = normalizeMaxRetries(options.maxRetries);\n434:   const retryCounts = normalizeRetryCountMap(options.initialRetryCounts);\n435:   const results = new Array(items.length);\n436:   const queue = items.map((_item, index) => index);\n437:   const lagCeilingMs = normalizeNonNegativeDuration(options.lagCeilingMs ?? options.lag_ceiling_ms ?? options.lag_ceiling);\n438:   const lagCeilingAction = normalizeLagCeilingAction(options.lagCeilingAction ?? options.lag_ceiling_action);\n439:   const shouldAbortStalledLineages = lagCeilingAction === LAG_CEILING_ACTION_ABORT_REQUEUE;\n440:   const postExitGraceMs = normalizeNonNegativeDuration(\n441:     options.postExitGraceMs ?? options.post_exit_grace_ms ?? options.postSubprocessExitGraceMs,\n442:   );\n443:   const postExitPollMs = normalizePositiveDuration(\n444:     options.postExitPollMs ?? options.post_exit_poll_ms,\n445:     postExitGraceMs > 0 ? Math.min(postExitGraceMs, 1000) : 1000,\n446:   );\n447:   const getAttemptLiveness = typeof options.getAttemptLiveness === 'function'\n448:     ? options.getAttemptLiveness\n449:     : null;\n450:   const shouldWatchPostExitOrphans = postExitGraceMs > 0 && getAttemptLiveness !== null;\n451:   if (shouldAbortStalledLineages && lagCeilingMs <= 0) {\n452:     throw new TypeError('lagCeilingAction \"abort-requeue\" requires lagCeilingMs > 0');\n453:   }\n454:   let lagCeilingTimer = null;\n455:   let postExitWatchdogTimer = null;\n456:   let lagCeilingExceeded = false;\n457:   let nextAttemptId = 1;\n458: \n459:   // STALL DETECTOR (not queue backpressure). The lag metric is the time since the pool\n460:   // last made progress — i.e. since the last item settled (or pool start if nothing has\n461:   // settled yet) — measured ONLY while work is still pending. On a healthy fan-out wider\n462:   // than its concurrency, items settle regularly, so each completion resets this clock and\n463:   // the gap stays small: normal second-wave backpressure does NOT trip the ceiling. The\n464:   // gap only grows past the ceiling when NOTHING settles while work waits — a genuinely\n465:   // stalled tail (a worker hung holding a slot). This deliberately replaces the prior\n466:   // time-since-queued-at-pool-start metric, which conflated normal backpressure with a\n467:   // stall and false-fired on every width>concurrency pool.\n468:   let lastProgressAtMs = Date.now();\n469:   const markProgress = () => {\n470:     lastProgressAtMs = Date.now();\n471:   };\n472: \n473:   const oldestPendingLagMs = () => {\n474:     // A stall is only meaningful while there is still queued work waiting for a slot.\n475:     if (lagCeilingMs <= 0 || queue.length === 0) return undefined;\n476:     return Date.now() - lastProgressAtMs;\n477:   };\n478: \n479:   const buildCurrentGauges = () => {\n480:     const settled = results.filter(Boolean).length;\n481:     const failed = results.filter((result) => result && result.status === 'rejected').length;\n482:     return buildPoolGauges({\n483:       total: items.length,\n484:       settled,\n485:       pending: queue.length,\n486:       failed,\n487:       oldestPendingLagMs: oldestPendingLagMs(),\n488:     });\n489:   };\n490: \n491:   return new Promise((resolve) => {\n492:     if (items.length === 0) {\n493:       resolve(buildPoolSummary(results));\n494:       return;\n495:     }\n496: \n497:     let active = 0;\n498:     let resolved = false;\n499:     const activeAttempts = new Map();\n500:     const clearLagCeilingTimer = () => {\n501:       if (lagCeilingTimer) {\n502:         clearTimeout(lagCeilingTimer);\n503:         lagCeilingTimer = null;\n504:       }\n505:     };\n506:     const clearPostExitWatchdogTimer = () => {\n507:       if (postExitWatchdogTimer) {\n508:         clearTimeout(postExitWatchdogTimer);\n509:         postExitWatchdogTimer = null;\n510:       }\n511:     };\n512: \n513:     const emitLagCeilingWarning = (gauges = buildCurrentGauges()) => {\n514:       if (!onEvent || lagCeilingMs <= 0 || lagCeilingExceeded || queue.length === 0) return;\n515:       if ((gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms ?? 0) < lagCeilingMs) return;\n516:       lagCeilingExceeded = true;\n517:       onEvent({\n518:         event: 'lag_ceiling_exceeded',\n519:         at: normalizeTimestamp(now()),\n520:         severity: 'warning',\n521:         ...(lagCeilingAction ? { action: lagCeilingAction } : {}),\n522:         // The lag metric is time-since-last-progress while work is pending: a genuine\n523:         // stall signal, not queue backpressure. oldest_pending_lag_ms keeps its name for\n524:         // ledger shape compatibility but now carries the stall duration.\n525:         metric: 'time_since_last_completion',\n526:         lag_ceiling_ms: lagCeilingMs,\n527:         oldest_pending_lag_ms: gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms,\n528:         gauges,\n529:       });\n530:     };\n531: \n532:     const scheduleLagCeilingCheck = () => {\n533:       clearLagCeilingTimer();\n534:       if (lagCeilingMs <= 0 || queue.length === 0) return;\n535:       if (!onEvent && !shouldAbortStalledLineages) return;\n536:       if (!shouldAbortStalledLineages && lagCeilingExceeded) return;\n537:       const lag = oldestPendingLagMs() ?? 0;\n538:       const delayMs = Math.max(0, lagCeilingMs - lag);\n539:       lagCeilingTimer = setTimeout(() => {\n540:         lagCeilingTimer = null;\n541:         handleLagCeilingExceeded();\n542:         if (!resolved) {\n543:           scheduleLagCeilingCheck();\n544:         }\n545:       }, delayMs);\n546:       lagCeilingTimer.unref?.();\n547:     };\n548: \n549:     const emitEvent = onEvent\n550:       ? (event) => {\n551:           onEvent({\n552:             ...event,\n553:             gauges: buildCurrentGauges(),\n554:           });\n555:           emitLagCeilingWarning();\n556:         }\n557:       : undefined;\n558: \n559:     const buildSyntheticAbortResult = (activeAttempt, gauges, error) => {\n560:       const lagMs = gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms ?? lagCeilingMs;\n561:       const completedAtIso = normalizeTimestamp(now());\n562:       const durationMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - activeAttempt.startedAtMs);\n563:       return {\n564:         label: activeAttempt.label,\n565:         status: 'rejected',\n566:         index: activeAttempt.index,\n567:         attempt: activeAttempt.attempt,\n568:         started_at_iso: activeAttempt.startedAtIso,\n569:         completed_at_iso: completedAtIso,\n570:         duration_ms: durationMs,\n571:         error: {\n572:           ...normalizeError(error),\n573:           aborted: true,\n574:           abort_reason: 'lag_ceiling_exceeded',\n575:         },\n576:       };\n577:     };\n578: \n579:     const buildPostExitOrphanResult = (activeAttempt, liveness, error) => {\n580:       const completedAtIso = normalizeTimestamp(now());\n581:       const durationMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - activeAttempt.startedAtMs);\n582:       return {\n583:         label: activeAttempt.label,\n584:         status: 'rejected',\n585:         index: activeAttempt.index,\n586:         attempt: activeAttempt.attempt,\n587:         started_at_iso: activeAttempt.startedAtIso,\n588:         completed_at_iso: completedAtIso,\n589:         duration_ms: durationMs,\n590:         error: {\n591:           ...normalizeError(error),\n592:           reason: POST_EXIT_ORPHAN_REASON,\n593:           post_exit_grace_ms: postExitGraceMs,\n594:           ...(Number.isInteger(liveness.pid) && liveness.pid > 0 ? { pid: liveness.pid } : {}),\n595:           ...(Number.isFinite(liveness.exitedAtMs) ? { subprocess_exited_at_ms: Math.floor(liveness.exitedAtMs) } : {}),\n596:         },\n597:       };\n598:     };\n599: \n600:     const emitSettledResult = (result, isTerminal) => {\n601:       if (!emitEvent) return;\n602:       const baseEvent = {\n603:         event: result.status === 'fulfilled' ? 'completed' : 'failed',\n604:         label: result.label,\n605:         index: result.index,\n606:         attempt: result.attempt,\n607:         at: result.completed_at_iso,\n608:         duration_ms: result.duration_ms,\n609:         terminal: isTerminal,\n610:       };\n611:       if (result.status === 'rejected') {\n612:         emitEvent({ ...baseEvent, error: result.error });\n613:       } else {\n614:         emitEvent(baseEvent);\n615:       }\n616:     };\n617: \n618:     const handleSettledResult = (activeAttempt, result) => {\n619:       const { index, label, retryCount } = activeAttempt;\n620:       result.index = index;\n621:       if (result.status === 'fulfilled') {\n622:         result.retry_attempts = retryCount;\n623:         results[index] = result;\n624:         emitSettledResult(result, true);\n625:         return;\n626:       }\n627: \n628:       const canRetry = result.error.retryable === true && retryCount < maxRetries;\n629:       if (canRetry) {\n630:         const nextRetryCount = retryCount + 1;\n631:         retryCounts.set(label, nextRetryCount);\n632:         emitSettledResult(result, false);\n633:         queue.push(index);\n634:         if (emitEvent) {\n635:           emitEvent({\n636:             event: 'retry_scheduled',\n637:             label,\n638:             index,\n639:             at: normalizeTimestamp(now()),\n640:             retry_count: nextRetryCount,\n641:             next_attempt: nextRetryCount + 1,\n642:             max_retries: maxRetries,\n643:             failure_class: result.error.failure_class,\n644:             retry_verdict: result.error.retry_verdict,\n645:           });\n646:         }\n647:         return;\n648:       }\n649: \n650:       result.retry_attempts = retryCount;\n651:       result.retry_exhausted = result.error.retryable === true && retryCount >= maxRetries;\n652:       results[index] = result;\n653:       emitSettledResult(result, true);\n654:     };\n655: \n656:     const buildPoolErrorResult = (activeAttempt, error) => ({\n657:       label: activeAttempt.label,\n658:       status: 'rejected',\n659:       index: activeAttempt.index,\n660:       attempt: activeAttempt.attempt,\n661:       started_at_iso: activeAttempt.startedAtIso,\n662:       completed_at_iso: normalizeTimestamp(now()),\n663:       duration_ms: Math.max(0, Date.now() - activeAttempt.startedAtMs),\n664:       error: normalizeError({ name: 'PoolError', message: String(error) }),\n665:     });\n666: \n667:     const settleActiveAttempt = (activeAttempt, result) => {\n668:       if (activeAttempt.settled) {\n669:         return;\n670:       }\n671:       activeAttempt.settled = true;\n672:       activeAttempts.delete(activeAttempt.id);\n673:       handleSettledResult(activeAttempt, result);\n674:       active -= 1;\n675:       // Every settlement (success, failure, or retry re-queue) is forward progress:\n676:       // reset the stall clock so a healthy pool's steady completions keep the lag\n677:       // metric small and only a true stall (no settlement) lets it grow.\n678:       markProgress();\n679:       scheduleLagCeilingCheck();\n680:       pump();\n681:     };\n682: \n683:     const abortStalledAttempt = (gauges) => {\n684:       if (!shouldAbortStalledLineages || activeAttempts.size === 0 || queue.length === 0) return false;\n685:       if ((gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms ?? 0) < lagCeilingMs) return false;\n686:       const activeAttempt = activeAttempts.values().next().value;\n687:       if (!activeAttempt || activeAttempt.settled) return false;\n688: \n689:       const error = buildLagCeilingTimeoutError({\n690:         label: activeAttempt.label,\n691:         lagMs: gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms ?? lagCeilingMs,\n692:         lagCeilingMs,\n693:       });\n694:       const result = buildSyntheticAbortResult(activeAttempt, gauges, error);\n695:       activeAttempt.abortController.abort(error);\n696:       if (onEvent) {\n697:         onEvent({\n698:           event: 'lag_ceiling_abort',\n699:           label: activeAttempt.label,\n\n(Showing lines 360-699 of 902. Use offset=700 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    onEvent({ event: 'started', label, index, attempt, at: startedAtIso });\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const baseContext = { index, label, attempt };\n    const workerContext = abortSignal ? { ...baseContext, signal: abortSignal } : baseContext;\n    const output = await worker(item, workerContext);\n    const completedAtIso = normalizeTimestamp(now());\n    const durationMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - startedAtMs);\n    if (emitSettledEvent && typeof onEvent === 'function') {\n      onEvent({ event: 'completed', label, index, attempt, at: completedAtIso, duration_ms: durationMs });\n    }\n    return {\n      label,\n      status: 'fulfilled',\n      attempt,\n      started_at_iso: startedAtIso,\n      completed_at_iso: completedAtIso,\n      duration_ms: durationMs,\n      output,","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs","text":"    onEvent({ event: 'started', label, index, attempt, at: startedAtIso });\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const baseContext = { index, label, attempt };\n    const workerContext = abortSignal ? { ...baseContext, signal: abortSignal } : baseContext;\n    const output = await worker(item, workerContext);\n    const completedAtIso = normalizeTimestamp(now());\n    const durationMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - startedAtMs);\n    if (emitSettledEvent && typeof onEvent === 'function') {\n      onEvent({ event: 'completed', label, index, attempt, at: completedAtIso, duration_ms: durationMs });\n    }\n    return {\n      label,\n      status: 'fulfilled',\n      attempt,\n      started_at_iso: startedAtIso,\n      completed_at_iso: completedAtIso,\n      duration_ms: durationMs,\n      output,\n    };\n  } catch (error) {\n    const completedAtIso = normalizeTimestamp(now());\n    const durationMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - startedAtMs);\n    const normalizedError = normalizeError(error);\n    if (emitSettledEvent && typeof onEvent === 'function') {\n      onEvent({ event: 'failed', label, index, attempt, at: completedAtIso, duration_ms: durationMs, error: normalizedError });\n    }\n    return {\n      label,\n      status: 'rejected',\n      attempt,\n      started_at_iso: startedAtIso,\n      completed_at_iso: completedAtIso,\n      duration_ms: durationMs,\n      error: normalizedError,\n    };\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Run items through a worker with at most `concurrency` in flight.\n *\n * This is the fan-out generalization of council `dispatchCouncilSeats`: same\n * never-throws per-item settlement and ordered results, plus a concurrency cap\n * so a large lineage set runs K-at-a-time (the proven `xargs -P K` shape).\n *\n * @param {Object} options - Pool configuration.\n * @param {Array} options.items - Work items (each ideally has a `label`).\n * @param {number} options.concurrency - Max items in flight (clamped to >= 1).\n * @param {Function} options.worker - Async worker: (item, { index, signal? }) => output.\n * @param {Function} [options.now] - Callable returning a Date/ISO timestamp.\n * @param {Function} [options.onEvent] - Optional ledger-event callback.\n * @param {string} [options.lagCeilingAction] - Optional `abort-requeue` action.\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} { results: [...ordered], summary: { total,\n *   succeeded, failed, all_failed } }.\n * @throws {TypeError} If items is not an array or worker is not a function.\n */\nfunction runCappedPool(options) {\n  if (!isRecord(options)) {\n    throw new TypeError('runCappedPool options must be an object');\n  }\n  const { items, worker } = options;\n  if (!Array.isArray(items)) {\n    throw new TypeError('items must be an array');\n  }\n  if (typeof worker !== 'function') {\n    throw new TypeError('worker must be a function');\n  }\n\n  const concurrency = normalizeConcurrency(options.concurrency);\n  const now = typeof options.now === 'function' ? options.now : () => new Date();\n  const onEvent = typeof options.onEvent === 'function' ? options.onEvent : undefined;\n  const maxRetries = normalizeMaxRetries(options.maxRetries);\n  const retryCounts = normalizeRetryCountMap(options.initialRetryCounts);\n  const results = new Array(items.length);\n  const queue = items.map((_item, index) => index);\n  const lagCeilingMs = normalizeNonNegativeDuration(options.lagCeilingMs ?? options.lag_ceiling_ms ?? options.lag_ceiling);\n  const lagCeilingAction = normalizeLagCeilingAction(options.lagCeilingAction ?? options.lag_ceiling_action);\n  const shouldAbortStalledLineages = lagCeilingAction === LAG_CEILING_ACTION_ABORT_REQUEUE;\n  const postExitGraceMs = normalizeNonNegativeDuration(\n    options.postExitGraceMs ?? options.post_exit_grace_ms ?? options.postSubprocessExitGraceMs,\n  );\n  const postExitPollMs = normalizePositiveDuration(\n    options.postExitPollMs ?? options.post_exit_poll_ms,\n    postExitGraceMs > 0 ? Math.min(postExitGraceMs, 1000) : 1000,\n  );\n  const getAttemptLiveness = typeof options.getAttemptLiveness === 'function'\n    ? options.getAttemptLiveness\n    : null;\n  const shouldWatchPostExitOrphans = postExitGraceMs > 0 && getAttemptLiveness !== null;\n  if (shouldAbortStalledLineages && lagCeilingMs <= 0) {\n    throw new TypeError('lagCeilingAction \"abort-requeue\" requires lagCeilingMs > 0');\n  }\n  let lagCeilingTimer = null;\n  let postExitWatchdogTimer = null;\n  let lagCeilingExceeded = false;\n  let nextAttemptId = 1;\n\n  // STALL DETECTOR (not queue backpressure). The lag metric is the time since the pool\n  // last made progress — i.e. since the last item settled (or pool start if nothing has\n  // settled yet) — measured ONLY while work is still pending. On a healthy fan-out wider\n  // than its concurrency, items settle regularly, so each completion resets this clock and\n  // the gap stays small: normal second-wave backpressure does NOT trip the ceiling. The\n  // gap only grows past the ceiling when NOTHING settles while work waits — a genuinely\n  // stalled tail (a worker hung holding a slot). This deliberately replaces the prior\n  // time-since-queued-at-pool-start metric, which conflated normal backpressure with a\n  // stall and false-fired on every width>concurrency pool.\n  let lastProgressAtMs = Date.now();\n  const markProgress = () => {\n    lastProgressAtMs = Date.now();\n  };\n\n  const oldestPendingLagMs = () => {\n    // A stall is only meaningful while there is still queued work waiting for a slot.\n    if (lagCeilingMs <= 0 || queue.length === 0) return undefined;\n    return Date.now() - lastProgressAtMs;\n  };\n\n  const buildCurrentGauges = () => {\n    const settled = results.filter(Boolean).length;\n    const failed = results.filter((result) => result && result.status === 'rejected').length;\n    return buildPoolGauges({\n      total: items.length,\n      settled,\n      pending: queue.length,\n      failed,\n      oldestPendingLagMs: oldestPendingLagMs(),\n    });\n  };\n\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    if (items.length === 0) {\n      resolve(buildPoolSummary(results));\n      return;\n    }\n\n    let active = 0;\n    let resolved = false;\n    const activeAttempts = new Map();\n    const clearLagCeilingTimer = () => {\n      if (lagCeilingTimer) {\n        clearTimeout(lagCeilingTimer);\n        lagCeilingTimer = null;\n      }\n    };\n    const clearPostExitWatchdogTimer = () => {\n      if (postExitWatchdogTimer) {\n        clearTimeout(postExitWatchdogTimer);\n        postExitWatchdogTimer = null;\n      }\n    };\n\n    const emitLagCeilingWarning = (gauges = buildCurrentGauges()) => {\n      if (!onEvent || lagCeilingMs <= 0 || lagCeilingExceeded || queue.length === 0) return;\n      if ((gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms ?? 0) < lagCeilingMs) return;\n      lagCeilingExceeded = true;\n      onEvent({\n        event: 'lag_ceiling_exceeded',\n        at: normalizeTimestamp(now()),\n        severity: 'warning',\n        ...(lagCeilingAction ? { action: lagCeilingAction } : {}),\n        // The lag metric is time-since-last-progress while work is pending: a genuine\n        // stall signal, not queue backpressure. oldest_pending_lag_ms keeps its name for\n        // ledger shape compatibility but now carries the stall duration.\n        metric: 'time_since_last_completion',\n        lag_ceiling_ms: lagCeilingMs,\n        oldest_pending_lag_ms: gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms,\n        gauges,\n      });\n    };\n\n    const scheduleLagCeilingCheck = () => {\n      clearLagCeilingTimer();\n      if (lagCeilingMs <= 0 || queue.length === 0) return;\n      if (!onEvent && !shouldAbortStalledLineages) return;\n      if (!shouldAbortStalledLineages && lagCeilingExceeded) return;\n      const lag = oldestPendingLagMs() ?? 0;\n      const delayMs = Math.max(0, lagCeilingMs - lag);\n      lagCeilingTimer = setTimeout(() => {\n        lagCeilingTimer = null;\n        handleLagCeilingExceeded();\n        if (!resolved) {\n          scheduleLagCeilingCheck();\n        }\n      }, delayMs);\n      lagCeilingTimer.unref?.();\n    };\n\n    const emitEvent = onEvent\n      ? (event) => {\n          onEvent({\n            ...event,\n            gauges: buildCurrentGauges(),\n          });\n          emitLagCeilingWarning();\n        }\n      : undefined;\n\n    const buildSyntheticAbortResult = (activeAttempt, gauges, error) => {\n      const lagMs = gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms ?? lagCeilingMs;\n      const completedAtIso = normalizeTimestamp(now());\n      const durationMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - activeAttempt.startedAtMs);\n      return {\n        label: activeAttempt.label,\n        status: 'rejected',\n        index: activeAttempt.index,\n        attempt: activeAttempt.attempt,\n        started_at_iso: activeAttempt.startedAtIso,\n        completed_at_iso: completedAtIso,\n        duration_ms: durationMs,\n        error: {\n          ...normalizeError(error),\n          aborted: true,\n          abort_reason: 'lag_ceiling_exceeded',\n        },\n      };\n    };\n\n    const buildPostExitOrphanResult = (activeAttempt, liveness, error) => {\n      const completedAtIso = normalizeTimestamp(now());\n      const durationMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - activeAttempt.startedAtMs);\n      return {\n        label: activeAttempt.label,\n        status: 'rejected',\n        index: activeAttempt.index,\n        attempt: activeAttempt.attempt,\n        started_at_iso: activeAttempt.startedAtIso,\n        completed_at_iso: completedAtIso,\n        duration_ms: durationMs,\n        error: {\n          ...normalizeError(error),\n          reason: POST_EXIT_ORPHAN_REASON,\n          post_exit_grace_ms: postExitGraceMs,\n          ...(Number.isInteger(liveness.pid) && liveness.pid > 0 ? { pid: liveness.pid } : {}),\n          ...(Number.isFinite(liveness.exitedAtMs) ? { subprocess_exited_at_ms: Math.floor(liveness.exitedAtMs) } : {}),\n        },\n      };\n    };\n\n    const emitSettledResult = (result, isTerminal) => {\n      if (!emitEvent) return;\n      const baseEvent = {\n        event: result.status === 'fulfilled' ? 'completed' : 'failed',\n        label: result.label,\n        index: result.index,\n        attempt: result.attempt,\n        at: result.completed_at_iso,\n        duration_ms: result.duration_ms,\n        terminal: isTerminal,\n      };\n      if (result.status === 'rejected') {\n        emitEvent({ ...baseEvent, error: result.error });\n      } else {\n        emitEvent(baseEvent);\n      }\n    };\n\n    const handleSettledResult = (activeAttempt, result) => {\n      const { index, label, retryCount } = activeAttempt;\n      result.index = index;\n      if (result.status === 'fulfilled') {\n        result.retry_attempts = retryCount;\n        results[index] = result;\n        emitSettledResult(result, true);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const canRetry = result.error.retryable === true && retryCount < maxRetries;\n      if (canRetry) {\n        const nextRetryCount = retryCount + 1;\n        retryCounts.set(label, nextRetryCount);\n        emitSettledResult(result, false);\n        queue.push(index);\n        if (emitEvent) {\n          emitEvent({\n            event: 'retry_scheduled',\n            label,\n            index,\n            at: normalizeTimestamp(now()),\n            retry_count: nextRetryCount,\n            next_attempt: nextRetryCount + 1,\n            max_retries: maxRetries,\n            failure_class: result.error.failure_class,\n            retry_verdict: result.error.retry_verdict,\n          });\n        }\n        return;\n      }\n\n      result.retry_attempts = retryCount;\n      result.retry_exhausted = result.error.retryable === true && retryCount >= maxRetries;\n      results[index] = result;\n      emitSettledResult(result, true);\n    };\n\n    const buildPoolErrorResult = (activeAttempt, error) => ({\n      label: activeAttempt.label,\n      status: 'rejected',\n      index: activeAttempt.index,\n      attempt: activeAttempt.attempt,\n      started_at_iso: activeAttempt.startedAtIso,\n      completed_at_iso: normalizeTimestamp(now()),\n      duration_ms: Math.max(0, Date.now() - activeAttempt.startedAtMs),\n      error: normalizeError({ name: 'PoolError', message: String(error) }),\n    });\n\n    const settleActiveAttempt = (activeAttempt, result) => {\n      if (activeAttempt.settled) {\n        return;\n      }\n      activeAttempt.settled = true;\n      activeAttempts.delete(activeAttempt.id);\n      handleSettledResult(activeAttempt, result);\n      active -= 1;\n      // Every settlement (success, failure, or retry re-queue) is forward progress:\n      // reset the stall clock so a healthy pool's steady completions keep the lag\n      // metric small and only a true stall (no settlement) lets it grow.\n      markProgress();\n      scheduleLagCeilingCheck();\n      pump();\n    };\n\n    const abortStalledAttempt = (gauges) => {\n      if (!shouldAbortStalledLineages || activeAttempts.size === 0 || queue.length === 0) return false;\n      if ((gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms ?? 0) < lagCeilingMs) return false;\n      const activeAttempt = activeAttempts.values().next().value;\n      if (!activeAttempt || activeAttempt.settled) return false;\n\n      const error = buildLagCeilingTimeoutError({\n        label: activeAttempt.label,\n        lagMs: gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms ?? lagCeilingMs,\n        lagCeilingMs,\n      });\n      const result = buildSyntheticAbortResult(activeAttempt, gauges, error);\n      activeAttempt.abortController.abort(error);\n      if (onEvent) {\n        onEvent({\n          event: 'lag_ceiling_abort',\n          label: activeAttempt.label,","lineStart":360,"lineEnd":699,"totalLines":902,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs","time":{"start":1783487537679,"end":1783487537683}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01d5aaabb52643db016a4ddc31981481918563211b4d2cdc11"}},"id":"prt_f402421e6001DhSmwVKh9P6ORI","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f4023ef4a001zy80pS5usrnE2X"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487537762,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_HGNwII29QmeBKDQDV5kEFxEr","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out Worker Pool                                   ║\n3: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n4: // ║ Concurrency-capped fan-out primitive for the opt-in multi-executor        ║\n5: // ║ (\"fan-out\") layer above the single-executor deep-loop. Generalizes the    ║\n6: // ║ council parallel dispatcher (lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs) by      ║\n7: // ║ adding a concurrency cap so N executor lineages run with at most K in      ║\n8: // ║ flight, plus a status-ledger writer following the proven                  ║\n9: // ║ orchestration-status.log ledger pattern.                                   ║\n10: // ║                                                                           ║\n11: // ║ Design: pure pool primitive (worker is INJECTED) + ledger helpers, fully  ║\n12: // ║ unit-tested. The real spawn worker and the CLI entry that wires it        ║\n13: // ║ (arg parse, JSON-out, exit codes) live in fanout-run.cjs.                ║\n14: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n15: \n16: 'use strict';\n17: \n18: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n19: // 1. IMPORTS\n20: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n21: \n22: const fs = require('node:fs');\n23: const path = require('node:path');\n24: const { classifyLineageFailure } = require('./lib/cli-guards.cjs');\n25: \n26: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n27: // 2. CONSTANTS\n28: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n29: \n30: const LAG_CEILING_ACTION_ABORT_REQUEUE = 'abort-requeue';\n31: const WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'wave';\n32: const WAVE_PLANNER_STATUS_DORMANT = 'dormant';\n33: const WAVE_PLANNER_DORMANT_MESSAGE = 'wave planner is dormant until conflict-safety substrate is available';\n34: const POST_EXIT_ORPHAN_REASON = 'orphaned_after_subprocess_exit';\n35: \n36: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n37: // 3. HELPERS\n38: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n39: \n40: function isRecord(value) {\n41:   return value !== null && typeof value === 'object' && !Array.isArray(value);\n42: }\n43: \n44: function normalizeTimestamp(value) {\n45:   if (value instanceof Date) {\n46:     return value.toISOString();\n47:   }\n48:   if (typeof value === 'string' && value.trim() !== '') {\n49:     return value;\n50:   }\n51:   return new Date().toISOString();\n52: }\n53: \n54: function normalizeConcurrency(value) {\n55:   const n = Number(value);\n56:   if (!Number.isFinite(n) || n < 1) {\n57:     return 1;\n58:   }\n59:   return Math.floor(n);\n60: }\n61: \n62: function labelFor(item, index) {\n63:   if (isRecord(item) && typeof item.label === 'string' && item.label.trim() !== '') {\n64:     return item.label;\n65:   }\n66:   return `item-${index}`;\n67: }\n68: \n69: function buildPoolGauges({ total, settled, pending, failed, oldestPendingLagMs }) {\n70:   const gauges = {\n71:     lag: Math.max(0, total - settled),\n72:     pending: Math.max(0, pending),\n73:     failed: Math.max(0, failed),\n74:   };\n75:   if (Number.isFinite(oldestPendingLagMs)) {\n76:     gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms = Math.max(0, Math.floor(oldestPendingLagMs));\n77:   }\n78:   return gauges;\n79: }\n80: \n81: function normalizeMaxRetries(value) {\n82:   if (value === undefined || value === null) {\n83:     return 0;\n84:   }\n85:   const n = Number(value);\n86:   if (!Number.isFinite(n) || n < 0) {\n87:     return 0;\n88:   }\n89:   return Math.floor(n);\n90: }\n91: \n92: function normalizeNonNegativeDuration(value) {\n93:   if (value === undefined || value === null) {\n94:     return 0;\n95:   }\n96:   const n = Number(value);\n97:   if (!Number.isFinite(n) || n < 0) {\n98:     return 0;\n99:   }\n100:   return Math.floor(n);\n101: }\n102: \n103: function normalizeLagCeilingAction(value) {\n104:   if (value === undefined || value === null || value === '') {\n105:     return null;\n106:   }\n107:   const action = String(value).trim();\n108:   if (action !== LAG_CEILING_ACTION_ABORT_REQUEUE) {\n109:     throw new TypeError('lagCeilingAction must be \"abort-requeue\" when set');\n110:   }\n111:   return action;\n112: }\n113: \n114: function normalizeRetryCountMap(value) {\n115:   const counts = new Map();\n116:   if (!isRecord(value)) {\n117:     return counts;\n118:   }\n119:   for (const [label, count] of Object.entries(value)) {\n120:     const n = Number(count);\n121:     if (typeof label === 'string' && label && Number.isFinite(n) && n > 0) {\n122:       counts.set(label, Math.floor(n));\n123:     }\n124:   }\n125:   return counts;\n126: }\n127: \n128: function buildFailureClassRollup(results) {\n129:   const rollup = {\n130:     timeout: 0,\n131:     exit: 0,\n132:     salvage_miss: 0,\n133:   };\n134:   for (const result of results) {\n135:     if (!result || result.status !== 'rejected') {\n136:       continue;\n137:     }\n138:     const failureClass = result.error && typeof result.error.failure_class === 'string'\n139:       ? result.error.failure_class\n140:       : 'exit';\n\n(Showing lines 1-140 of 902. Use offset=141 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out Worker Pool                                   ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Concurrency-capped fan-out primitive for the opt-in multi-executor        ║\n// ║ (\"fan-out\") layer above the single-executor deep-loop. Generalizes the    ║\n// ║ council parallel dispatcher (lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs) by      ║\n// ║ adding a concurrency cap so N executor lineages run with at most K in      ║\n// ║ flight, plus a status-ledger writer following the proven                  ║\n// ║ orchestration-status.log ledger pattern.                                   ║\n// ║                                                                           ║\n// ║ Design: pure pool primitive (worker is INJECTED) + ledger helpers, fully  ║\n// ║ unit-tested. The real spawn worker and the CLI entry that wires it        ║\n// ║ (arg parse, JSON-out, exit codes) live in fanout-run.cjs.                ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out Worker Pool                                   ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Concurrency-capped fan-out primitive for the opt-in multi-executor        ║\n// ║ (\"fan-out\") layer above the single-executor deep-loop. Generalizes the    ║\n// ║ council parallel dispatcher (lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs) by      ║\n// ║ adding a concurrency cap so N executor lineages run with at most K in      ║\n// ║ flight, plus a status-ledger writer following the proven                  ║\n// ║ orchestration-status.log ledger pattern.                                   ║\n// ║                                                                           ║\n// ║ Design: pure pool primitive (worker is INJECTED) + ledger helpers, fully  ║\n// ║ unit-tested. The real spawn worker and the CLI entry that wires it        ║\n// ║ (arg parse, JSON-out, exit codes) live in fanout-run.cjs.                ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { classifyLineageFailure } = require('./lib/cli-guards.cjs');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst LAG_CEILING_ACTION_ABORT_REQUEUE = 'abort-requeue';\nconst WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'wave';\nconst WAVE_PLANNER_STATUS_DORMANT = 'dormant';\nconst WAVE_PLANNER_DORMANT_MESSAGE = 'wave planner is dormant until conflict-safety substrate is available';\nconst POST_EXIT_ORPHAN_REASON = 'orphaned_after_subprocess_exit';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. HELPERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction isRecord(value) {\n  return value !== null && typeof value === 'object' && !Array.isArray(value);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeTimestamp(value) {\n  if (value instanceof Date) {\n    return value.toISOString();\n  }\n  if (typeof value === 'string' && value.trim() !== '') {\n    return value;\n  }\n  return new Date().toISOString();\n}\n\nfunction normalizeConcurrency(value) {\n  const n = Number(value);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(n) || n < 1) {\n    return 1;\n  }\n  return Math.floor(n);\n}\n\nfunction labelFor(item, index) {\n  if (isRecord(item) && typeof item.label === 'string' && item.label.trim() !== '') {\n    return item.label;\n  }\n  return `item-${index}`;\n}\n\nfunction buildPoolGauges({ total, settled, pending, failed, oldestPendingLagMs }) {\n  const gauges = {\n    lag: Math.max(0, total - settled),\n    pending: Math.max(0, pending),\n    failed: Math.max(0, failed),\n  };\n  if (Number.isFinite(oldestPendingLagMs)) {\n    gauges.oldest_pending_lag_ms = Math.max(0, Math.floor(oldestPendingLagMs));\n  }\n  return gauges;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeMaxRetries(value) {\n  if (value === undefined || value === null) {\n    return 0;\n  }\n  const n = Number(value);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(n) || n < 0) {\n    return 0;\n  }\n  return Math.floor(n);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeNonNegativeDuration(value) {\n  if (value === undefined || value === null) {\n    return 0;\n  }\n  const n = Number(value);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(n) || n < 0) {\n    return 0;\n  }\n  return Math.floor(n);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeLagCeilingAction(value) {\n  if (value === undefined || value === null || value === '') {\n    return null;\n  }\n  const action = String(value).trim();\n  if (action !== LAG_CEILING_ACTION_ABORT_REQUEUE) {\n    throw new TypeError('lagCeilingAction must be \"abort-requeue\" when set');\n  }\n  return action;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeRetryCountMap(value) {\n  const counts = new Map();\n  if (!isRecord(value)) {\n    return counts;\n  }\n  for (const [label, count] of Object.entries(value)) {\n    const n = Number(count);\n    if (typeof label === 'string' && label && Number.isFinite(n) && n > 0) {\n      counts.set(label, Math.floor(n));\n    }\n  }\n  return counts;\n}\n\nfunction buildFailureClassRollup(results) {\n  const rollup = {\n    timeout: 0,\n    exit: 0,\n    salvage_miss: 0,\n  };\n  for (const result of results) {\n    if (!result || result.status !== 'rejected') {\n      continue;\n    }\n    const failureClass = result.error && typeof result.error.failure_class === 'string'\n      ? result.error.failure_class\n      : 'exit';","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":140,"totalLines":902,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs","time":{"start":1783487537757,"end":1783487537761}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01d5aaabb52643db016a4ddc31982c8191885b76d96a97ecc9"}},"id":"prt_f4024221e001c8Qce1sPyQxtPp","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f4023ef4a001zy80pS5usrnE2X"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487537794,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_EC7QN6x3hx9pKm0jo4AgbNlY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":1180,"limit":210},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1180:     timer.unref?.();\n1181:   };\n1182: \n1183:   schedule();\n1184:   return () => {\n1185:     fired = true;\n1186:     if (timer) clearTimeout(timer);\n1187:   };\n1188: }\n1189: \n1190: /**\n1191:  * Run a lineage subprocess without blocking the Node event loop.\n1192:  *\n1193:  * Resolves a spawnSync-shaped result ({ status, signal, stdout, error }) so the\n1194:  * pool's K-in-flight cap actually overlaps lineages. spawnSync blocked the single\n1195:  * thread until each child exited, serializing every lineage regardless of the\n1196:  * concurrency cap; an awaited async spawn yields to the loop so K run at once.\n1197:  *\n1198:  * On timeout the child is killed with SIGTERM and result.signal is set to\n1199:  * 'SIGTERM', preserving the timeout-as-failure signal the caller relies on.\n1200:  *\n1201:  * @param {string} command - Executable to run.\n1202:  * @param {string[]} cmdArgs - Arguments for the executable.\n1203:  * @param {Object} opts - { cwd, env, timeoutMs, maxBuffer, input? }.\n1204:  * @returns {Promise<{status:number|null, signal:string|null, stdout:string, error?:Error}>}\n1205:  */\n1206: function runLineageProcess(command, cmdArgs, opts) {\n1207:   const { cwd, env, timeoutMs, maxBuffer } = opts;\n1208:   const hasInput = typeof opts.input === 'string';\n1209: \n1210:   return new Promise((resolvePromise) => {\n1211:     let child;\n1212:     try {\n1213:       child = spawn(command, cmdArgs, {\n1214:         cwd,\n1215:         env,\n1216:         stdio: [hasInput ? 'pipe' : 'ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n1217:         detached: process.platform !== 'win32',\n1218:       });\n1219:     } catch (error) {\n1220:       resolvePromise({ status: null, signal: null, stdout: '', error });\n1221:       return;\n1222:     }\n1223:     activeLineageProcesses.add(child);\n1224:     if (typeof opts.onSpawn === 'function') {\n1225:       opts.onSpawn({ pid: child.pid });\n1226:     }\n1227: \n1228:     let stdout = '';\n1229:     let stdoutBytes = 0;\n1230:     let truncated = false;\n1231:     let timedOut = false;\n1232:     let settled = false;\n1233:     let spawnError;\n1234: \n1235:     const timer = setTimeout(() => {\n1236:       timedOut = true;\n1237:       terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n1238:     }, timeoutMs);\n1239:     timer.unref?.();\n1240: \n1241:     const abortHandler = () => {\n1242:       terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n1243:     };\n1244:     if (opts.abortSignal) {\n1245:       if (opts.abortSignal.aborted) {\n1246:         abortHandler();\n1247:       } else {\n1248:         opts.abortSignal.addEventListener('abort', abortHandler, { once: true });\n1249:       }\n1250:     }\n1251: \n1252:     child.stdout?.setEncoding('utf8');\n1253:     child.stdout?.on('data', (chunk) => {\n1254:       if (truncated) return;\n1255:       stdoutBytes += Buffer.byteLength(chunk, 'utf8');\n1256:       if (stdoutBytes > maxBuffer) {\n1257:         truncated = true;\n1258:         terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n1259:         return;\n1260:       }\n1261:       stdout += chunk;\n1262:     });\n1263:     // Drain stderr so the child never blocks on a full pipe; we do not capture it.\n1264:     child.stderr?.resume();\n1265: \n1266:     child.on('error', (error) => {\n1267:       spawnError = error;\n1268:     });\n1269: \n1270:     child.on('close', (code, signal) => {\n1271:       if (settled) return;\n1272:       settled = true;\n1273:       activeLineageProcesses.delete(child);\n1274:       clearTimeout(timer);\n1275:       opts.abortSignal?.removeEventListener?.('abort', abortHandler);\n1276:       const effectiveSignal = timedOut ? 'SIGTERM' : signal;\n1277:       if (typeof opts.onExit === 'function') {\n1278:         opts.onExit({ status: timedOut ? null : code, signal: effectiveSignal, pid: child.pid, exitedAtMs: Date.now() });\n1279:       }\n1280:       resolvePromise({\n1281:         status: timedOut ? null : code,\n1282:         signal: effectiveSignal,\n1283:         stdout,\n1284:         ...(spawnError ? { error: spawnError } : {}),\n1285:       });\n1286:     });\n1287: \n1288:     if (hasInput) {\n1289:       child.stdin?.on('error', () => {});\n1290:       child.stdin?.end(opts.input);\n1291:     }\n1292:   });\n1293: }\n1294: \n1295: /**\n1296:  * Build the subprocess command for a fan-out lineage.\n1297:  * Returns { command, args, input?, env } where input is stdin content when applicable.\n1298:  */\n1299: function buildLineageCommand(lineage, prompt, resolvedSandbox, resolvedPermission, options = {}) {\n1300:   const kind = lineage.kind;\n1301: \n1302:   if (kind === 'cli-claude-code') {\n1303:     const args = [\n1304:       '-p',\n1305:       prompt,\n1306:       '--model',\n1307:       lineage.model || 'claude-opus-4-8',\n1308:       '--permission-mode',\n1309:       resolvedPermission,\n1310:       '--output-format',\n1311:       'text',\n1312:     ];\n1313:     if (lineage.reasoningEffort) {\n1314:       args.push('--effort', lineage.reasoningEffort);\n1315:     }\n1316:     return { command: 'claude', args };\n1317:   }\n1318: \n1319:   if (kind === 'native') {\n1320:     // Native fan-out cannot call the LEAF @deep-review agent with a full-loop prompt.\n1321:     // For review runs this is the real deep/review command surface with a lineage\n1322:     // artifact override, so the command YAML owns init, loop, and synthesis.\n1323:     const args = [\n1324:       'run',\n1325:       '--format',\n1326:       'json',\n1327:       '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n1328:       '--dir',\n1329:       process.cwd(),\n1330:       '--command',\n1331:       `deep/${options.loopType || 'review'}`,\n1332:     ];\n1333:     args.push(buildNativeCommandInput(\n1334:       options.loopType || 'review',\n1335:       options.specFolder || '',\n1336:       options.lineageDir || '',\n1337:       lineage,\n1338:       options,\n1339:     ));\n1340:     return { command: 'opencode', args, input: '' };\n1341:   }\n1342: \n1343:   if (kind === 'cli-opencode') {\n1344:     // No --agent: current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it\n1345:     // on a top-level `run`. The default agent runs when none is named, and a\n1346:     // specific agent profile can be requested in the prompt body instead.\n1347:     const args = [\n1348:       'run',\n1349:       '--model',\n1350:       lineage.model || 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-8',\n1351:       '--format',\n1352:       'json',\n1353:       '--pure',\n1354:       '--dir',\n1355:       process.cwd(),\n1356:     ];\n1357:     // Permission bypass is opt-in: only detach the sandbox for lineages that explicitly\n1358:     // request danger-full-access. workspace-write/read-only lineages run WITHOUT\n1359:     // --dangerously-skip-permissions so their writes are subject to the CLI permission\n1360:     // boundary. opencode has no path-scoped write flag, so a workspace-write review\n1361:     // lineage's lineageDir-only boundary still relies on the prompt — but the operator\n1362:     // must now opt into full bypass rather than getting it silently by default.\n1363:     const useDangerousBypass = resolvedSandbox === 'danger-full-access';\n1364:     if (useDangerousBypass) {\n1365:       args.splice(args.indexOf('--pure'), 0, '--dangerously-skip-permissions');\n1366:       process.stderr.write(\n1367:         `FATAL WARN: lineage ${lineage.label || '(cli-opencode)'} runs with --dangerously-skip-permissions. `\n1368:           + `The lineageDir write boundary is prompt-only, not sandbox-enforced.\\n`,\n1369:       );\n1370:     }\n1371:     if (lineage.reasoningEffort) {\n1372:       args.push('--variant', lineage.reasoningEffort);\n1373:     }\n1374:     args.push(prompt);\n1375:     return { command: 'opencode', args, input: '' };\n1376:   }\n1377: \n1378:   throw inputError(`Unknown fan-out executor kind: ${kind}`);\n1379: }\n1380: \n1381: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1382: // 4. CORE LOGIC\n1383: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1384: \n1385: async function main() {\n1386:   const args = parseArgs();\n1387:   const specFolder = validateNamespaceValue(ensureString(args, 'specFolder'), 'specFolder', inputError);\n1388:   const loopType = ensureString(args, 'loopType');\n1389:   assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType);\n\n(Showing lines 1180-1389 of 1871. Use offset=1390 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    timer.unref?.();\n  };\n\n  schedule();\n  return () => {\n    fired = true;\n    if (timer) clearTimeout(timer);\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Run a lineage subprocess without blocking the Node event loop.\n *\n * Resolves a spawnSync-shaped result ({ status, signal, stdout, error }) so the\n * pool's K-in-flight cap actually overlaps lineages. spawnSync blocked the single\n * thread until each child exited, serializing every lineage regardless of the\n * concurrency cap; an awaited async spawn yields to the loop so K run at once.\n *\n * On timeout the child is killed with SIGTERM and result.signal is set to\n * 'SIGTERM', preserving the timeout-as-failure signal the caller relies on.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","text":"    timer.unref?.();\n  };\n\n  schedule();\n  return () => {\n    fired = true;\n    if (timer) clearTimeout(timer);\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Run a lineage subprocess without blocking the Node event loop.\n *\n * Resolves a spawnSync-shaped result ({ status, signal, stdout, error }) so the\n * pool's K-in-flight cap actually overlaps lineages. spawnSync blocked the single\n * thread until each child exited, serializing every lineage regardless of the\n * concurrency cap; an awaited async spawn yields to the loop so K run at once.\n *\n * On timeout the child is killed with SIGTERM and result.signal is set to\n * 'SIGTERM', preserving the timeout-as-failure signal the caller relies on.\n *\n * @param {string} command - Executable to run.\n * @param {string[]} cmdArgs - Arguments for the executable.\n * @param {Object} opts - { cwd, env, timeoutMs, maxBuffer, input? }.\n * @returns {Promise<{status:number|null, signal:string|null, stdout:string, error?:Error}>}\n */\nfunction runLineageProcess(command, cmdArgs, opts) {\n  const { cwd, env, timeoutMs, maxBuffer } = opts;\n  const hasInput = typeof opts.input === 'string';\n\n  return new Promise((resolvePromise) => {\n    let child;\n    try {\n      child = spawn(command, cmdArgs, {\n        cwd,\n        env,\n        stdio: [hasInput ? 'pipe' : 'ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n        detached: process.platform !== 'win32',\n      });\n    } catch (error) {\n      resolvePromise({ status: null, signal: null, stdout: '', error });\n      return;\n    }\n    activeLineageProcesses.add(child);\n    if (typeof opts.onSpawn === 'function') {\n      opts.onSpawn({ pid: child.pid });\n    }\n\n    let stdout = '';\n    let stdoutBytes = 0;\n    let truncated = false;\n    let timedOut = false;\n    let settled = false;\n    let spawnError;\n\n    const timer = setTimeout(() => {\n      timedOut = true;\n      terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n    }, timeoutMs);\n    timer.unref?.();\n\n    const abortHandler = () => {\n      terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n    };\n    if (opts.abortSignal) {\n      if (opts.abortSignal.aborted) {\n        abortHandler();\n      } else {\n        opts.abortSignal.addEventListener('abort', abortHandler, { once: true });\n      }\n    }\n\n    child.stdout?.setEncoding('utf8');\n    child.stdout?.on('data', (chunk) => {\n      if (truncated) return;\n      stdoutBytes += Buffer.byteLength(chunk, 'utf8');\n      if (stdoutBytes > maxBuffer) {\n        truncated = true;\n        terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n        return;\n      }\n      stdout += chunk;\n    });\n    // Drain stderr so the child never blocks on a full pipe; we do not capture it.\n    child.stderr?.resume();\n\n    child.on('error', (error) => {\n      spawnError = error;\n    });\n\n    child.on('close', (code, signal) => {\n      if (settled) return;\n      settled = true;\n      activeLineageProcesses.delete(child);\n      clearTimeout(timer);\n      opts.abortSignal?.removeEventListener?.('abort', abortHandler);\n      const effectiveSignal = timedOut ? 'SIGTERM' : signal;\n      if (typeof opts.onExit === 'function') {\n        opts.onExit({ status: timedOut ? null : code, signal: effectiveSignal, pid: child.pid, exitedAtMs: Date.now() });\n      }\n      resolvePromise({\n        status: timedOut ? null : code,\n        signal: effectiveSignal,\n        stdout,\n        ...(spawnError ? { error: spawnError } : {}),\n      });\n    });\n\n    if (hasInput) {\n      child.stdin?.on('error', () => {});\n      child.stdin?.end(opts.input);\n    }\n  });\n}\n\n/**\n * Build the subprocess command for a fan-out lineage.\n * Returns { command, args, input?, env } where input is stdin content when applicable.\n */\nfunction buildLineageCommand(lineage, prompt, resolvedSandbox, resolvedPermission, options = {}) {\n  const kind = lineage.kind;\n\n  if (kind === 'cli-claude-code') {\n    const args = [\n      '-p',\n      prompt,\n      '--model',\n      lineage.model || 'claude-opus-4-8',\n      '--permission-mode',\n      resolvedPermission,\n      '--output-format',\n      'text',\n    ];\n    if (lineage.reasoningEffort) {\n      args.push('--effort', lineage.reasoningEffort);\n    }\n    return { command: 'claude', args };\n  }\n\n  if (kind === 'native') {\n    // Native fan-out cannot call the LEAF @deep-review agent with a full-loop prompt.\n    // For review runs this is the real deep/review command surface with a lineage\n    // artifact override, so the command YAML owns init, loop, and synthesis.\n    const args = [\n      'run',\n      '--format',\n      'json',\n      '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n      '--dir',\n      process.cwd(),\n      '--command',\n      `deep/${options.loopType || 'review'}`,\n    ];\n    args.push(buildNativeCommandInput(\n      options.loopType || 'review',\n      options.specFolder || '',\n      options.lineageDir || '',\n      lineage,\n      options,\n    ));\n    return { command: 'opencode', args, input: '' };\n  }\n\n  if (kind === 'cli-opencode') {\n    // No --agent: current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it\n    // on a top-level `run`. The default agent runs when none is named, and a\n    // specific agent profile can be requested in the prompt body instead.\n    const args = [\n      'run',\n      '--model',\n      lineage.model || 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-8',\n      '--format',\n      'json',\n      '--pure',\n      '--dir',\n      process.cwd(),\n    ];\n    // Permission bypass is opt-in: only detach the sandbox for lineages that explicitly\n    // request danger-full-access. workspace-write/read-only lineages run WITHOUT\n    // --dangerously-skip-permissions so their writes are subject to the CLI permission\n    // boundary. opencode has no path-scoped write flag, so a workspace-write review\n    // lineage's lineageDir-only boundary still relies on the prompt — but the operator\n    // must now opt into full bypass rather than getting it silently by default.\n    const useDangerousBypass = resolvedSandbox === 'danger-full-access';\n    if (useDangerousBypass) {\n      args.splice(args.indexOf('--pure'), 0, '--dangerously-skip-permissions');\n      process.stderr.write(\n        `FATAL WARN: lineage ${lineage.label || '(cli-opencode)'} runs with --dangerously-skip-permissions. `\n          + `The lineageDir write boundary is prompt-only, not sandbox-enforced.\\n`,\n      );\n    }\n    if (lineage.reasoningEffort) {\n      args.push('--variant', lineage.reasoningEffort);\n    }\n    args.push(prompt);\n    return { command: 'opencode', args, input: '' };\n  }\n\n  throw inputError(`Unknown fan-out executor kind: ${kind}`);\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. CORE LOGIC\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nasync function main() {\n  const args = parseArgs();\n  const specFolder = validateNamespaceValue(ensureString(args, 'specFolder'), 'specFolder', inputError);\n  const loopType = ensureString(args, 'loopType');\n  assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType);","lineStart":1180,"lineEnd":1389,"totalLines":1871,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","time":{"start":1783487537785,"end":1783487537793}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01d5aaabb52643db016a4ddc3198388191ba0ae6f4f16a8e58"}},"id":"prt_f40242265001kSuOSwtRJfclEG","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f4023ef4a001zy80pS5usrnE2X"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487537811,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1qqmrAjCDiTqppbZ4gIA7tcv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":1390,"limit":170},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1390:   // Optional shared research question, threaded into each lineage prompt so a research\n1391:   // fan-out can bind research_topic. Absent for review, which scopes by folder.\n1392:   const researchTopic = typeof args.researchTopic === 'string' && args.researchTopic.trim()\n1393:     ? args.researchTopic.trim()\n1394:     : null;\n1395:   const fanoutConfigJson = ensureString(args, 'fanoutConfigJson');\n1396:   const baseArtifactDir = validateBaseArtifactDir(ensureString(args, 'baseArtifactDir'), specFolder, loopType);\n1397:   const convergenceThreshold = parseOptionalNumber(args, 'convergenceThreshold');\n1398:   const lineageTimeoutHoursOverride = parseOptionalNumber(args, 'lineageTimeoutHours');\n1399:   const stopPolicy = normalizeStopPolicy(args.stopPolicy);\n1400: \n1401:   const {\n1402:     parseFanoutConfig,\n1403:     expandLineages,\n1404:     resolveSandboxMode,\n1405:     resolveClaudePermissionMode,\n1406:   } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts');\n1407:   const { buildExecutorDispatchEnv, detectSameKindFromStack, CLI_DISPATCH_STACK_ENV } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts');\n1408:   const {\n1409:     DEFAULT_LINEAGE_TIMESTAMP_TOLERANCE_MS,\n1410:     checkLineageTimestampWindow,\n1411:   } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/lineage-timestamp-window.ts');\n1412: \n1413:   maybeThrowTestFault();\n1414: \n1415:   let rawConfig;\n1416:   try {\n1417:     rawConfig = JSON.parse(fanoutConfigJson);\n1418:   } catch {\n1419:     throw inputError('fanoutConfigJson is not valid JSON');\n1420:   }\n1421: \n1422:   const lineagesDir = path.join(baseArtifactDir, 'lineages');\n1423:   const ledgerPath = path.join(baseArtifactDir, 'orchestration-status.log');\n1424:   const summaryPath = path.join(baseArtifactDir, 'orchestration-summary.json');\n1425:   const runId = `${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8)}`;\n1426:   const parsedFanoutConfig = parseFanoutConfig(rawConfig);\n1427:   const rawGuardConfig = rawConfigWithCliBudgetOverrides(rawConfig, args);\n1428:   const stallWatchdogMs = normalizeStallWatchdogMs(rawGuardConfig);\n1429:   const lineageBudgetGuards = normalizeLineageBudgetGuards(rawGuardConfig);\n1430:   const guardedAssignment = applyFlatPoolAssignmentGuard(parsedFanoutConfig);\n1431:   const fanoutConfig = guardedAssignment.config;\n1432:   const allLineages = expandLineages(fanoutConfig);\n1433:   const progressHeartbeatMs = normalizeProgressHeartbeatMs(fanoutConfig.progressHeartbeatSeconds);\n1434:   const postExitGraceMs = normalizePostExitGraceMs(rawGuardConfig, progressHeartbeatMs);\n1435:   const slotIntervalMs = progressHeartbeatMs;\n1436: \n1437:   logFlatPoolGuardRejections({\n1438:     rejections: guardedAssignment.rejections,\n1439:     ledgerPath,\n1440:     runId,\n1441:     loopType,\n1442:     specFolder,\n1443:   });\n1444: \n1445:   // Fan-out pool owns every lineage kind. The old YAML-native branch dispatched the\n1446:   // LEAF review agent with a full-loop prompt, which is invalid; keep full-loop\n1447:   // ownership here so all lineages share the same retries and artifact validation.\n1448:   const cliLineages = allLineages;\n1449:   const checkpointPath = waitCheckpointPath(baseArtifactDir);\n1450:   const resumeWaiting = await resumeWaitingCheckpoint({\n1451:     checkpointPath,\n1452:     ledgerPath,\n1453:     runId,\n1454:     loopType,\n1455:     specFolder,\n1456:   });\n1457:   if (!resumeWaiting.didWait) {\n1458:     await persistPreDispatchWait({\n1459:       checkpointPath,\n1460:       ledgerPath,\n1461:       runId,\n1462:       loopType,\n1463:       specFolder,\n1464:       waitMs: args.preDispatchWaitMs,\n1465:     });\n1466:   }\n1467: \n1468:   if (cliLineages.length === 0) {\n1469:     const summary = {\n1470:       total: 0,\n1471:       succeeded: 0,\n1472:       failed: 0,\n1473:       all_failed: false,\n1474:       gauges: { lag: 0, pending: 0, failed: 0 },\n1475:       convergence: { status: 'converged', reason: 'empty_tick', no_new_findings: true },\n1476:     };\n1477:     writeOrchestrationSummary(summaryPath, {\n1478:       run_id: runId,\n1479:       loop_type: loopType,\n1480:       spec_folder: specFolder,\n1481:       base_artifact_dir: baseArtifactDir,\n1482:       total_cli_lineages: 0,\n1483:       ...summary,\n1484:     });\n1485:     jsonOut({ status: 'ok', message: 'no CLI lineages to spawn', run_id: runId, results: [], summary });\n1486:     return;\n1487:   }\n1488: \n1489:   fs.mkdirSync(lineagesDir, { recursive: true });\n1490:   const orphanedLineages = markOrphanedLineages(ledgerPath);\n1491:   const initialRetryCounts = readRetryCountsFromLedger(ledgerPath);\n1492: \n1493:   const lineageSnapshots = new Map();\n1494:   const lineageSlotAccounting = new Map();\n1495:   const lineageProcessLiveness = new Map();\n1496:   let latestGauges = { lag: cliLineages.length, pending: cliLineages.length, failed: 0 };\n1497:   let stoppedSummaryWritten = false;\n1498: \n1499:   const writeStoppedSummary = (signal) => {\n1500:     if (stoppedSummaryWritten) return;\n1501:     stoppedSummaryWritten = true;\n1502:     stopActiveLineageProcesses(signal);\n1503:     const stoppedAtIso = new Date().toISOString();\n1504:     const partial = summarizeSnapshots(cliLineages, lineageSnapshots);\n1505:     const gauges = {\n1506:       lag: latestGauges.lag,\n1507:       pending: latestGauges.pending,\n1508:       failed: Math.max(latestGauges.failed, partial.summary.failed),\n1509:     };\n1510:     appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n1511:       event: 'stopped',\n1512:       signal,\n1513:       at: stoppedAtIso,\n1514:       gauges,\n1515:     });\n1516:     writeOrchestrationSummary(summaryPath, {\n1517:       run_id: runId,\n1518:       loop_type: loopType,\n1519:       spec_folder: specFolder,\n1520:       base_artifact_dir: baseArtifactDir,\n1521:       total_cli_lineages: cliLineages.length,\n1522:       stopped: true,\n1523:       stopped_signal: signal,\n1524:       stopped_at_iso: stoppedAtIso,\n1525:       status: 'partial',\n1526:       ...partial.summary,\n1527:       gauges,\n1528:       results: partial.results,\n1529:     });\n1530:   };\n1531: \n1532:   installFanoutSignalHandlers(writeStoppedSummary);\n1533: \n1534:   const { results, summary } = await runCappedPool({\n1535:     items: cliLineages,\n1536:     concurrency: fanoutConfig.concurrency,\n1537:     maxRetries: fanoutConfig.maxRetries,\n1538:     lagCeilingMs: fanoutConfig.lagCeilingMs,\n1539:     postExitGraceMs,\n1540:     initialRetryCounts,\n1541:     getAttemptLiveness: (attempt) => lineageProcessLiveness.get(`${attempt.label}:${attempt.attempt}`) ?? { alive: true },\n1542:     onEvent: (event) => {\n1543:       const enrichedEvent = decorateSlotAccountingEvent(event, lineageSlotAccounting);\n1544:       updateLineageSnapshot(lineageSnapshots, enrichedEvent);\n1545:       if (enrichedEvent.gauges) latestGauges = enrichedEvent.gauges;\n1546:       appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, enrichedEvent);\n1547:     },\n1548:     worker: async (lineage, context) => {\n1549:       const slotWindowStartIso = new Date().toISOString();\n1550:       const hrStart = process.hrtime();\n1551:       const attempt = Number.isFinite(Number(context.attempt)) ? Number(context.attempt) : 1;\n1552:       const livenessKey = `${lineage.label}:${attempt}`;\n1553:       const lineageDir = path.join(lineagesDir, lineage.label);\n1554:       const stateDir = path.join(lineageDir, '.executor-state');\n1555:       fs.mkdirSync(lineageDir, { recursive: true });\n1556:       fs.mkdirSync(stateDir, { recursive: true });\n1557: \n1558:       const budgetDecision = evaluateLineageBudgetCap({ lineage, guards: lineageBudgetGuards });\n1559:       if (!budgetDecision.continue_allowed) {\n\n(Showing lines 1390-1559 of 1871. Use offset=1560 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  // Optional shared research question, threaded into each lineage prompt so a research\n  // fan-out can bind research_topic. Absent for review, which scopes by folder.\n  const researchTopic = typeof args.researchTopic === 'string' && args.researchTopic.trim()\n    ? args.researchTopic.trim()\n    : null;\n  const fanoutConfigJson = ensureString(args, 'fanoutConfigJson');\n  const baseArtifactDir = validateBaseArtifactDir(ensureString(args, 'baseArtifactDir'), specFolder, loopType);\n  const convergenceThreshold = parseOptionalNumber(args, 'convergenceThreshold');\n  const lineageTimeoutHoursOverride = parseOptionalNumber(args, 'lineageTimeoutHours');\n  const stopPolicy = normalizeStopPolicy(args.stopPolicy);\n\n  const {\n    parseFanoutConfig,\n    expandLineages,\n    resolveSandboxMode,\n    resolveClaudePermissionMode,\n  } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts');\n  const { buildExecutorDispatchEnv, detectSameKindFromStack, CLI_DISPATCH_STACK_ENV } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts');\n  const {\n    DEFAULT_LINEAGE_TIMESTAMP_TOLERANCE_MS,","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","text":"  // Optional shared research question, threaded into each lineage prompt so a research\n  // fan-out can bind research_topic. Absent for review, which scopes by folder.\n  const researchTopic = typeof args.researchTopic === 'string' && args.researchTopic.trim()\n    ? args.researchTopic.trim()\n    : null;\n  const fanoutConfigJson = ensureString(args, 'fanoutConfigJson');\n  const baseArtifactDir = validateBaseArtifactDir(ensureString(args, 'baseArtifactDir'), specFolder, loopType);\n  const convergenceThreshold = parseOptionalNumber(args, 'convergenceThreshold');\n  const lineageTimeoutHoursOverride = parseOptionalNumber(args, 'lineageTimeoutHours');\n  const stopPolicy = normalizeStopPolicy(args.stopPolicy);\n\n  const {\n    parseFanoutConfig,\n    expandLineages,\n    resolveSandboxMode,\n    resolveClaudePermissionMode,\n  } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts');\n  const { buildExecutorDispatchEnv, detectSameKindFromStack, CLI_DISPATCH_STACK_ENV } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts');\n  const {\n    DEFAULT_LINEAGE_TIMESTAMP_TOLERANCE_MS,\n    checkLineageTimestampWindow,\n  } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/lineage-timestamp-window.ts');\n\n  maybeThrowTestFault();\n\n  let rawConfig;\n  try {\n    rawConfig = JSON.parse(fanoutConfigJson);\n  } catch {\n    throw inputError('fanoutConfigJson is not valid JSON');\n  }\n\n  const lineagesDir = path.join(baseArtifactDir, 'lineages');\n  const ledgerPath = path.join(baseArtifactDir, 'orchestration-status.log');\n  const summaryPath = path.join(baseArtifactDir, 'orchestration-summary.json');\n  const runId = `${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8)}`;\n  const parsedFanoutConfig = parseFanoutConfig(rawConfig);\n  const rawGuardConfig = rawConfigWithCliBudgetOverrides(rawConfig, args);\n  const stallWatchdogMs = normalizeStallWatchdogMs(rawGuardConfig);\n  const lineageBudgetGuards = normalizeLineageBudgetGuards(rawGuardConfig);\n  const guardedAssignment = applyFlatPoolAssignmentGuard(parsedFanoutConfig);\n  const fanoutConfig = guardedAssignment.config;\n  const allLineages = expandLineages(fanoutConfig);\n  const progressHeartbeatMs = normalizeProgressHeartbeatMs(fanoutConfig.progressHeartbeatSeconds);\n  const postExitGraceMs = normalizePostExitGraceMs(rawGuardConfig, progressHeartbeatMs);\n  const slotIntervalMs = progressHeartbeatMs;\n\n  logFlatPoolGuardRejections({\n    rejections: guardedAssignment.rejections,\n    ledgerPath,\n    runId,\n    loopType,\n    specFolder,\n  });\n\n  // Fan-out pool owns every lineage kind. The old YAML-native branch dispatched the\n  // LEAF review agent with a full-loop prompt, which is invalid; keep full-loop\n  // ownership here so all lineages share the same retries and artifact validation.\n  const cliLineages = allLineages;\n  const checkpointPath = waitCheckpointPath(baseArtifactDir);\n  const resumeWaiting = await resumeWaitingCheckpoint({\n    checkpointPath,\n    ledgerPath,\n    runId,\n    loopType,\n    specFolder,\n  });\n  if (!resumeWaiting.didWait) {\n    await persistPreDispatchWait({\n      checkpointPath,\n      ledgerPath,\n      runId,\n      loopType,\n      specFolder,\n      waitMs: args.preDispatchWaitMs,\n    });\n  }\n\n  if (cliLineages.length === 0) {\n    const summary = {\n      total: 0,\n      succeeded: 0,\n      failed: 0,\n      all_failed: false,\n      gauges: { lag: 0, pending: 0, failed: 0 },\n      convergence: { status: 'converged', reason: 'empty_tick', no_new_findings: true },\n    };\n    writeOrchestrationSummary(summaryPath, {\n      run_id: runId,\n      loop_type: loopType,\n      spec_folder: specFolder,\n      base_artifact_dir: baseArtifactDir,\n      total_cli_lineages: 0,\n      ...summary,\n    });\n    jsonOut({ status: 'ok', message: 'no CLI lineages to spawn', run_id: runId, results: [], summary });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  fs.mkdirSync(lineagesDir, { recursive: true });\n  const orphanedLineages = markOrphanedLineages(ledgerPath);\n  const initialRetryCounts = readRetryCountsFromLedger(ledgerPath);\n\n  const lineageSnapshots = new Map();\n  const lineageSlotAccounting = new Map();\n  const lineageProcessLiveness = new Map();\n  let latestGauges = { lag: cliLineages.length, pending: cliLineages.length, failed: 0 };\n  let stoppedSummaryWritten = false;\n\n  const writeStoppedSummary = (signal) => {\n    if (stoppedSummaryWritten) return;\n    stoppedSummaryWritten = true;\n    stopActiveLineageProcesses(signal);\n    const stoppedAtIso = new Date().toISOString();\n    const partial = summarizeSnapshots(cliLineages, lineageSnapshots);\n    const gauges = {\n      lag: latestGauges.lag,\n      pending: latestGauges.pending,\n      failed: Math.max(latestGauges.failed, partial.summary.failed),\n    };\n    appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n      event: 'stopped',\n      signal,\n      at: stoppedAtIso,\n      gauges,\n    });\n    writeOrchestrationSummary(summaryPath, {\n      run_id: runId,\n      loop_type: loopType,\n      spec_folder: specFolder,\n      base_artifact_dir: baseArtifactDir,\n      total_cli_lineages: cliLineages.length,\n      stopped: true,\n      stopped_signal: signal,\n      stopped_at_iso: stoppedAtIso,\n      status: 'partial',\n      ...partial.summary,\n      gauges,\n      results: partial.results,\n    });\n  };\n\n  installFanoutSignalHandlers(writeStoppedSummary);\n\n  const { results, summary } = await runCappedPool({\n    items: cliLineages,\n    concurrency: fanoutConfig.concurrency,\n    maxRetries: fanoutConfig.maxRetries,\n    lagCeilingMs: fanoutConfig.lagCeilingMs,\n    postExitGraceMs,\n    initialRetryCounts,\n    getAttemptLiveness: (attempt) => lineageProcessLiveness.get(`${attempt.label}:${attempt.attempt}`) ?? { alive: true },\n    onEvent: (event) => {\n      const enrichedEvent = decorateSlotAccountingEvent(event, lineageSlotAccounting);\n      updateLineageSnapshot(lineageSnapshots, enrichedEvent);\n      if (enrichedEvent.gauges) latestGauges = enrichedEvent.gauges;\n      appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, enrichedEvent);\n    },\n    worker: async (lineage, context) => {\n      const slotWindowStartIso = new Date().toISOString();\n      const hrStart = process.hrtime();\n      const attempt = Number.isFinite(Number(context.attempt)) ? Number(context.attempt) : 1;\n      const livenessKey = `${lineage.label}:${attempt}`;\n      const lineageDir = path.join(lineagesDir, lineage.label);\n      const stateDir = path.join(lineageDir, '.executor-state');\n      fs.mkdirSync(lineageDir, { recursive: true });\n      fs.mkdirSync(stateDir, { recursive: true });\n\n      const budgetDecision = evaluateLineageBudgetCap({ lineage, guards: lineageBudgetGuards });\n      if (!budgetDecision.continue_allowed) {","lineStart":1390,"lineEnd":1559,"totalLines":1871,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","time":{"start":1783487537807,"end":1783487537811}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01d5aaabb52643db016a4ddc3198408191819822991f16534f"}},"id":"prt_f4024227a001gGnQmwZe234x1B","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f4023ef4a001zy80pS5usrnE2X"}}
