{"type":"text","timestamp":1783487710753,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"id":"prt_f4026a131001zT3ZqWhpjftvyC","messageID":"msg_f40266a63001cQMZaP8OBreA47","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","type":"text","text":"The specs confirm this phase is read-only investigation plus lineage artifact writes, with the merge itself out of scope. I’m checking actual runtime/workflow code now for the structural seams, path classes, and fallback behavior.","time":{"start":1783487701297,"end":1783487710751},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_09609c5706403a57016a4ddcd5475081918d23c25dabb6b1e3","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487710796,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_8p3FIO0QxUlCQSs0Txr88XSi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime|system-spec-kit/shared|resolveArtifactRoot|fallback-router|MiMo|mimo|glm","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime","include":"*.{cjs,ts,json,md}"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/vitest.config.ts:\n  Line 1: // MODULE: deep-loop-runtime Vitest Config\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 4:   \"skill_id\": \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n\n  Line 18:         \"target\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 23:         \"target\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 28:         \"target\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 35:         \"target\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 40:         \"target\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 45:         \"target\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 53:         \"target\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 55:         \"context\": \"frozen MCP-free backend that deep-loop-workflows consumes for every mode\"\n\n  Line 64:       \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 65:       \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 66:       \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 82:     \"deep-loop-runtime skill\",\n\n  Line 91:       \"deep-loop-runtime skill\",\n\n  Line 98:       \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n\n  Line 112:       \"fallback-router\",\n\n  Line 120:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md\",\n\n  Line 121:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md\",\n\n  Line 122:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts\",\n\n  Line 123:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts\",\n\n  Line 124:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs\",\n\n  Line 125:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/round-state-jsonl.cjs\",\n\n  Line 126:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/adjudicator-verdict-scoring.cjs\",\n\n  Line 127:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/cost-guards.cjs\",\n\n  Line 128:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/session-state-hierarchy.cjs\",\n\n  Line 129:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs\",\n\n  Line 130:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs\",\n\n  Line 131:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite\",\n\n  Line 132:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-config.vitest.ts\",\n\n  Line 133:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/council/multi-seat-dispatch.vitest.ts\",\n\n  Line 134:       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/council/round-state-jsonl.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 138:         \"name\": \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n\n  Line 140:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md\",\n\n  Line 146:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts\",\n\n  Line 150:         \"name\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 152:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\",\n\n  Line 156:         \"name\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 158:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\",\n\n  Line 164:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs\",\n\n  Line 170:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs\",\n\n  Line 176:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/query.cjs\",\n\n  Line 182:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/status.cjs\",\n\n  Line 188:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs\",\n\n  Line 194:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/round-state-jsonl.cjs\",\n\n  Line 200:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/adjudicator-verdict-scoring.cjs\",\n\n  Line 206:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/cost-guards.cjs\",\n\n  Line 212:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/session-state-hierarchy.cjs\",\n\n  Line 216:         \"name\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 218:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md\",\n\n  Line 224:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:\n  Line 2: name: deep-loop-runtime\n\n  Line 32: - A deep-review or deep-research workflow YAML invokes `node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/<name>.cjs`\n\n  Line 33: - A test file imports `from '.../deep-loop-runtime/lib/...'`\n\n  Line 56:   *\"deep-loop runtime\"*|*\"deep-loop-runtime\"*|*\"executor config\"*|*\"prompt pack\"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;\n\n  Line 206: - `fallback-router.ts` — executor fallback decision matrix\n\n  Line 224: The Runtime Boundary Decision (ADR-001) extends `deep-loop-runtime/lib/` with council-compatible infrastructure primitives while keeping operator-facing and domain workflow semantics in `deep-ai-council`. These primitives are consumed by downstream deep-ai-council orchestration (per-topic multi-round, session-findings registry, command and skill wiring, parity and cost docs) for per-topic orchestration, multi-topic session state, command wiring, parity tests and docs.\n\n  Line 267: The system-spec-kit `mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` so a single vitest run discovers both surfaces.\n\n  Line 354: - **system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts** includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` for cross-package test discovery.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"deep-loop-runtime\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Shared runtime library the active deep-loop-workflows modes ride: executor dispatch, prompt-pack rendering, atomic state, coverage-graph storage, Bayesian convergence scoring and council durability, consumed through TypeScript imports and direct .cjs script calls.\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"deep-loop-runtime\"\n\n  Line 17: # deep-loop-runtime\n\n  Line 29: | **Works on** | The one consumer skill that imports it, `deep-loop-workflows`, across active modes: `research`, `review`, `ai-council` and `improvement`. Legacy `context` parsing remains only for historical artifacts. |\n\n  Line 44: `deep-loop-runtime` provides three component families through TypeScript imports under `lib/` and `.cjs` script entry points under `scripts/`, plus shared lifecycle, observability, and test-harness helpers surfaced in the catalog. The deep-loop family owns executor config, prompt-pack rendering, post-dispatch validation, atomic state, JSONL repair, loop locking, permissions gating, Bayesian scoring and fallback routing. It also hosts the shared backend contracts the consumer modes ride: a parameterized capability resolver, the artifact-topology seam (`resolveArtifactRoot`), the terminal lifecycle taxonomy (seven `stopReason` plus four `sessionOutcome` values) and a CLI adapter over the loop lock. The coverage-graph family owns the SQLite schema, query builders and convergence-signal extraction. The council family owns multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator-verdict scoring, cost guards, session-state hierarchy and the council graph. The workflow modes import what they need. No mode invokes this skill directly, and none of these contracts register an MCP tool. It is the foundation they ride.\n\n  Line 53: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs \\\n\n  Line 64: import { acquireLoopLock, releaseLoopLock } from '../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/loop-lock.js';\n\n  Line 65: import { renderPromptPack } from '../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.js';\n\n  Line 66: import { validateIterationOutputs } from '../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.js';\n\n  Line 81: pnpm --dir .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server exec vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests\n\n  Line 92: `lib/deep-loop/` holds the loop infrastructure. `executor-config` parses per-iteration executor settings from a shared schema so every consumer calls the same executor shape. `executor-audit` appends a provenance block to each iteration JSONL so you can tell which model and CLI produced each iteration. `prompt-pack` renders the iteration prompt template. `post-dispatch-validate` checks that an iteration produced valid markdown, JSONL and delta outputs before the state log accepts them, stamps seekable log-region offsets, and quarantines failed LLM-judge fallback cards. `atomic-state` writes state logs through a tmpfile-plus-rename pattern, adds compare-before-write, SHA-256 integrity helpers, and a deferred writer, so a crash never leaves a partial line and unchanged snapshots can avoid redundant writes. `jsonl-repair` recovers a corrupt trailing line before append and supports lock-held fan-out salvage merges. `loop-lock` enforces single-writer access around state mutations, with heartbeat metadata and opt-in host-local single-flight acquisition. `permissions-gate` checks permission scope before touching sensitive paths. `bayesian-scorer` exports the small Bayesian helpers `computeScore` and `shouldDemote`; `convergence.cjs` builds the typed loop decisions. `fallback-router` picks a replacement executor when the primary one times out and validates typed reroute graphs before dispatch.\n\n  Line 116: `deep-loop-runtime` is the foundation. The `deep-loop-workflows` skill is the building, and its active modes are the rooms that ride the runtime.\n\n  Line 152: A: One: `deep-loop-workflows`, across active modes (`research`, `review`, `ai-council` and `improvement`). Each mode imports the modules it needs and calls the `.cjs` scripts from its workflow YAML. The deprecated context loop is not an active consumer; retained `context` handling is for historical artifacts only. The runtime itself has no user-facing command and registers no MCP tools.\n\n  Line 185: python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/validate_document.py .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md --type readme\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"deep-loop-runtime: Manual Testing Playbook\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Operator-facing reference combining the manual testing directory, integrated review protocol, execution expectations, and per-feature validation files for the deep-loop-runtime skill.\"\n\n  Line 7: # deep-loop-runtime: Manual Testing Playbook\n\n  Line 11: This document combines the operator-facing manual validation contract for the `deep-loop-runtime` skill into a single reference. The root playbook acts as the directory, review protocol, and orchestration guide while per-feature files carry scenario-specific execution truth.\n\n  Line 34: This playbook provides 52 deterministic scenarios across 12 categories validating the current `deep-loop-runtime` skill surface. Each scenario maps to one feature catalog entry and one dedicated scenario file with objective, prompt, execution steps, source anchors, and verdict criteria.\n\n  Line 48: - `deep-loop-runtime` exists at `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`.\n\n  Line 71: - Script invocations use `node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/<name>.cjs ...`.\n\n  Line 116: Prompt: `Validate Executor config and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 129: Prompt: `Validate Executor audit and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 142: Prompt: `Validate Fallback router and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 147: > **Feature File:** [DLR-003](01--executor/fallback-router.md)\n\n  Line 157: Prompt: `Validate Fallback-router typed reroute and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 162: > **Feature File:** [DLR-044](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md)\n\n  Line 176: Prompt: `Validate Prompt pack and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 195: Prompt: `Validate Post-dispatch validate and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 210: Prompt: `Validate LLM-judge hardening and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 244: Prompt: `Validate Atomic state and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 257: Prompt: `Validate JSONL repair and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 270: Prompt: `Validate Loop lock and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 283: Prompt: `Validate Permissions gate and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 298: Prompt: `Validate Atomic-state serialize-diff and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 311: Prompt: `Validate Atomic-state integrity helpers and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 324: Prompt: `Validate Atomic-state deferred writer and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 337: Prompt: `Validate JSONL lock-held merge and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 350: Prompt: `Validate Loop-lock heartbeat hardening and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n  Line 363: Prompt: `Validate Loop-lock single-flight decision and report whether the current source, script surface, and tests agree with the deep-loop-runtime contract.`\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime|system-spec-kit/shared|resolveArtifactRoot|fallback-router|MiMo|mimo|glm","time":{"start":1783487710780,"end":1783487710794}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09609c5706403a57016a4ddcdeb4c88191877483495682b4ed"}},"id":"prt_f4026c6200015oUD5T8KSmAQiI","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f40266a63001cQMZaP8OBreA47"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487710841,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_TaU7XP3A5NXt5VYzrefqo3qW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"deep-loop-runtime|deep-loop-workflows|system-spec-kit/shared|resolveArtifactRoot|runtime/|fallback-router","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows","include":"*.{cjs,ts,json,md}"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/hub-router.json:\n  Line 2:   \"skill\": \"deep-loop-workflows\",\n\n  Line 54:       \"keywords\": [\"deep-loop-workflows\", \"deep-loop\", \"deep loop\", \"mode-registry\", \"workflowmode\", \"runtimeloop-type\", \"backendkind\", \"convergence-detection\", \"externalized-state\", \"runtime-loop\", \"improvement-host\"]\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:\n  Line 2: name: deep-loop-workflows\n\n  Line 4: description: \"Unified deep-loop workflow skill: routes active requests to research, review, ai-council, and improvement modes over the shared deep-loop-runtime backend.\"\n\n  Line 8: <!-- Keywords: deep-loop-workflows, deep-loop, deep-research, deep-review, deep-ai-council, deep-improvement, context-gathering, reuse-catalog, autoresearch, iterative-research, review-loop, deep-review-wave, release-readiness, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, ai-council, council-deliberation, multi-seat-planning, agent-improvement, benchmark-harness, model-benchmark, skill-benchmark, non-dev-ai-system, convergence-detection, externalized-state, coverage-graph, mode-registry, workflowmode, runtimeloop-type, backendkind -->\n\n  Line 12: One skill, four active workflow families, one shared backend. `deep-loop-workflows` is the public, advisor-routable home for active deep-loop personas; `deep-loop-runtime` is the frozen, MCP-free backend it consumes. This hub holds NO per-mode convergence, state, or synthesis logic — each active mode keeps its own contract in its packet, and the hub only routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json`.\n\n  Line 20: Use this skill (through the hub) for any active deep-loop workflow. Invoke it as `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)` (optionally with a mode hint such as `research: <request>`); the hub classifies the request, resolves a `workflowMode`, and loads the matching nested mode packet. Active `/deep:*` commands and native agent types remain as complementary surfaces over the same packets.\n\n  Line 24: | **research** | Outward, web + code iterative investigation → `research/research.md` | `deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/` | `/deep:research` | `deep-research` |\n\n  Line 25: | **review** | Iterative review loop → P0/P1/P2 findings + verdict | `deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/` | `/deep:review` | `deep-review` |\n\n  Line 26: | **ai-council** | Multi-seat planning deliberation → `ai-council/**` artifacts | `deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/` | `/deep:ai-council` | `ai-council` |\n\n  Line 27: | **improvement** (4 lanes) | Evaluator-first improvement: `agent-improvement`, `model-benchmark`, `skill-benchmark`, `non-dev-ai-system-refine` | `deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/` | `/deep:agent-improvement` · `/deep:model-benchmark` · `/deep:skill-benchmark` · `/deep:ai-system-improvement` | `deep-improvement` |\n\n  Line 31: - Backend/runtime support (executor, coverage-graph, scoring, fan-out) — that is `deep-loop-runtime`, consumed here, not invoked as a user workflow.\n\n  Line 37: Routing is **registry-driven** (invokable-hub, Option E). `mode-registry.json` is the single source of truth; the hub reads it and does not re-derive the mapping. When invoked as `Skill(deep-loop-workflows[, \"<mode>: <request>\"])`, the hub classifies the request to a `workflowMode`, resolves it through the registry, and loads `registry[mode].packet`. The advisor routes any deep-loop query to the single identity `deep-loop-workflows`; the hub then picks the mode. The `/deep:*` commands and native agent types remain as complementary surfaces — they reach the same packets through static routers/agent definitions — and the hub holds NO per-mode logic.\n\n  Line 43: - **`runtimeLoopType`** — the graph-backed convergence key consumed by `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` (validated against active `research|review|council`). **Explicit `null` for all four improvement lanes; never inferred from `workflowMode`.** Note `ai-council` maps to `runtimeLoopType: council`.\n\n  Line 56:        e.g. registry[\"research\"].packet → deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n\n  Line 57:        (the 4 improvement modes all share the deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/ packet)\n\n  Line 74: deep-loop-workflows/\n\n  Line 85: All modes consume `deep-loop-runtime` (frozen, MCP-free): executor config, prompt-pack, validation, atomic state, coverage-graph, Bayesian scoring, fan-out, the council primitives, and the promoted plumbing (capability resolver, artifact-root, loop-lock CLI, lifecycle taxonomy). The runtime never gains an `improvement` loopType — improvement stays host-driven.\n\n  Line 95: - **ALWAYS** keep exactly one `graph-metadata.json` (this hub's) so the advisor sees one skill identity, whether a mode is reached via `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)`, a `/deep:*` command, or an agent.\n\n  Line 96: - **ALWAYS** keep `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)` hub routing, the `/deep:*` commands, and the agent types as complementary surfaces over the same packets — never let one surface fork per-mode logic out of its packet.\n\n  Line 99: - **NEVER** add an `improvement` `loopType` to `deep-loop-runtime/convergence.cjs` (improvement is host-driven; `runtimeLoopType` stays `null`).\n\n  Line 112: - Backend: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` (frozen, consumed by every mode).\n\n  Line 123: - `Skill(deep-loop-workflows[, hint])` reaches a mode, and the `/deep:*` commands and agent types still reach the same packets.\n\n  Line 137: - `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)` is the invokable hub; active `/deep:*` commands and the agent types (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `ai-council`, `deep-improvement`) are complementary surfaces over the same packets.\n\n  Line 138: - `deep-loop-runtime` is the frozen, MCP-free backend every mode consumes.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/README.md:\n  Line 74: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs specs/042-pipeline \\\n\n  Line 83: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/advise-council-completion.cjs specs/042-pipeline\n\n  Line 128: The council shares the `deep-loop-runtime` with the other active deep-loop families. The current active roster is research, review, ai-council and improvement; each owns a different phase of the planning-to-implementation pipeline and none crosses into another's territory. Use `@context` or `/speckit:plan` for codebase context before council work.\n\n  Line 145: | `deep-loop-runtime` | Shared runtime for the active deep-loop families. Council graph support is a derived projection rebuilt from artifacts through the runtime's CLI scripts. |\n\n  Line 194: | README structure | `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/validate_document.py .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/README.md --type readme` reports zero issues |\n\n  Line 195: | Skill package structure | `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/quick_validate.py .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council` exits 0 |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/README.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"deep-loop-workflows\"\n\n  Line 11: # deep-loop-workflows\n\n  Line 22: | **Invoke with** | `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)`, the