laybook\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Operator-facing reference for manually validating deep-loop-workflows hub routing, advisor integration, backend discrimination, state discipline, and per-mode artifact ownership against the live skill registry.\"\n\n  Line 7: # deep-loop-workflows: Manual Testing Playbook\n\n  Line 9: > **EXECUTION POLICY**: Every scenario MUST be executed against the live `deep-loop-workflows` skill and its real `mode-registry.json` source of truth. No mocks, no stubs, and no invented routing behavior. Acceptable verdicts are PASS, PARTIAL, FAIL, or SKIP with a documented sandbox blocker.\n\n  Line 11: This document combines the manual-validation contract for the `deep-loop-workflows` parent-skill hub into a single operator reference. The root playbook acts as the directory, review protocol, and orchestration guide. Per-feature files provide the deeper execution contract for each scenario, including the user request, expected mode, command, agent, backend, artifact root, registry evidence, and binary validation criteria.\n\n  Line 29: This playbook provides 20 deterministic scenarios across 5 categories validating the `deep-loop-workflows` parent-skill hub. Each feature keeps its stable `{PREFIX}-NNN` ID and links to a dedicated feature file with the full execution contract.\n\n  Line 35: - Advisor integration: the single advisor identity `deep-loop-workflows`, lexical scoring, alias-fold default behavior, command-bridge behavior, and no false fire on ordinary code-edit prompts.\n\n  Line 41: 1. A realistic user request is given to an orchestrator that has the `deep-loop-workflows` skill registered.\n\n  Line 60: 2. The hub skill is present at `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/`.\n\n  Line 61: 3. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md` states that `mode-registry.json` is the single source of truth and that the hub holds no per-mode convergence, state, or synthesis logic.\n\n  Line 62: 4. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json` contains exactly 7 active modes in its `modes` array.\n\n  Line 64: 6. The orchestrator runtime can invoke `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)` and can run `/deep:*` command prompts, or the operator can capture equivalent dry-run routing transcripts.\n\n  Line 86: - Skill hub invocation: `Skill(deep-loop-workflows, \"<prompt>\")`.\n\n  Line 88: - Registry check: read `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json` and compare the selected mode to the matching `modes[]` entry.\n\n  Line 89: - Resource path notation: paths shown relative to `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/` unless explicitly stated otherwise.\n\n  Line 166: | `AI-001` | Single Advisor Identity | Positive deep-loop controls surface `deep-loop-workflows` as the hub identity | `03--advisor-integration/single-advisor-identity.md` | Yes |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/assets/runtime_capabilities.json:\n  Line 27:     \"quickValidate\": \"python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/quick_validate.py .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council --json\",\n\n  Line 28:     \"completionAdvisory\": \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/advise-council-completion.cjs <packet>\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/changelog/v2.4.0.0.md:\n  Line 19: The packet path moves from `deep-loop-workflows/ai-council/` to `deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/`. What stays the same: the `workflowMode` key, the `/deep:ai-council` command, the `@ai-council` agent and the `<packet>/ai-council/` artifact root. Only the skill packet path changed, so no command, agent or stored-artifact path breaks.\n\n  Line 27: | `deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/**` | Renamed from `ai-council/` so the folder matches the SKILL.md name. The name field and internal path references were updated to match. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:\n  Line 97: No new top-level commands ship in this release. The agent is dispatched through normal Task delegation patterns, and the persistence helper at `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/persist-artifacts.cjs` runs as a CLI wrapper for callers that need to persist a captured council report from outside the agent context.\n\n  Line 108: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md`                                   | Created — sk-doc template aligned, 8 numbered sections, 4-pattern smart router, 8-intent routing model   |\n\n  Line 109: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/README.md`                                  | Created — HVR style, 10 numbered sections, 252 lines                                                     |\n\n  Line 110: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/description.json`                           | Created — discovery metadata, version 1.0.0                                                              |\n\n  Line 111: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/graph-metadata.json`                        | Created — skill graph node, depends-on system-spec-kit, sibling deep-research                            |\n\n  Line 112: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/references/output_schema.md`                | Created — markdown report contract for the persistence parser                                            |\n\n  Line 113: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/references/folder_layout.md`                | Created — packet-local artifact tree                                                                     |\n\n  Line 114: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/references/state_format.md`                 | Created — append-only JSONL event semantics   