    expect(resolveFallback('missing-model', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', null))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 128:     const router = createFallbackRouter(registry);\n\n  Line 163:     expect(() => createFallbackRouter(registry)).toThrow(\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:\n  Line 12: import { type ModelProfile, type ModelRegistry, resolveFallback } from '../../lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.js';\n\n  Line 237: describe('fallback-router approval guard (008)', () => {\n\n  Line 245:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry, ['swe-1.6', 'haiku'])).toEqual({\n\n  Line 253:     const route = resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry, ['swe-1.6']);\n\n  Line 259:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry)).toEqual({\n","metadata":{"matches":24,"truncated":false},"title":"resolveFallback|createFallbackRouter|validateFallbackGraph|fallback-router","time":{"start":1783487742207,"end":1783487742219}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052459e0b1e9bdef016a4ddcfe1dfc8191b4cf93385bf2121a"}},"id":"prt_f402740fd001UrZerrDKSAohsC","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f402702d4001mwmUsz8AwO4zF7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487742245,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_aUVld7IMOMw2JPkmm0WmGPda","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"mimo|MiMo|glm|GLM|xiaomi|zai-coding-plan|token-plan|fallback","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:\n  Line 11:   - \"mimo dispatch scaffold\"\n\n  Line 490: **When**: dispatching to the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token alternative `minimax/MiniMax-M3` via the Direct API). The 120/003 benchmark (real MiniMax M2.7 runs) found MiniMax diverges from the cross-model defaults: **TIDD-EC** framework + **dense** pre-planning wins (RCAF + medium is the fallback) — carry this contract forward to M3 until re-benchmarked. `--variant` is omitted by default (unverified). **Omit `--agent`** (rejected on opencode 1.15.13).\n\n  Line 535: ## 16. TEMPLATE 15 — MiMo (XIAOMI TOKEN PLAN + DIRECT API; COSTAR + LEAN)\n\n  Line 537: **When**: dispatching to MiMo-V2.5-Pro via the Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — primary slug `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` (provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams`, quota pool `xiaomi-token-plan`) — or via the Xiaomi Direct API — slugs `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` and the low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` (provider `xiaomi`, pay-per-token; pick UltraSpeed for latency-sensitive checks/smokes — same COSTAR contract). The 126/004 benchmark (10/10 real `mimo-v2.5-pro` runs) found **COSTAR wins** (RACE is a statistical-tie fallback); use **lean-to-medium** pre-planning. MiMo is frontier-correct already, so frame for format + brevity, **not** guardrails — TIDD-EC/dense ranked LAST, and CIDI is unreliable (it intermittently writes to a file instead of returning inline code). **Always pass `--variant high`** — opencode maps low/medium/high to MiMo's reasoning effort (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13); high is the standing default. **Omit `--agent`** (on opencode 1.15.13 `--agent general` warns and falls back to the default agent). Confirm live model ids with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Token Plan) or `opencode models xiaomi` (Direct API).\n\n  Line 543:   --model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro \\\n\n  Line 551: **Invocation (Direct API — pay-per-token; swap in `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` for the low-latency tier)**:\n\n  Line 555:   --model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro \\\n\n  Line 563: **Prompt scaffold (COSTAR — empirical winner)**: Context (task + repo facts) → Objective (the single concrete deliverable) → Style (`precise, no preamble`) → Tone (neutral) → Audience (`an automated/downstream consumer that parses your output`) → Response (exact output shape, e.g. \"return ONLY the function body\"). Keep pre-planning lean-to-medium. **RACE** (Role/Action/Context/Expectation) is the equally-valid fallback. Do NOT use TIDD-EC or dense guardrail framing — it ranked last for MiMo (inflated output ~2.4× and leaked explanatory prose that broke the code-only contract).\n\n  Line 565: **Why**: MiMo-V2.5-Pro (1M-token context, strongly agentic — 1000+ tool calls, token-efficient; SWE-bench Pro 57.2) is an explicitly-selectable model on the Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) and the Xiaomi Direct API; the default skill model stays `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`. The COSTAR/RACE-lean contract is the empirical 004 finding (10/10 real dispatches; the discriminator was format adherence + token efficiency, not correctness — MiMo solved every fixture under every framework). Evidence: `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/benchmarks/004-mimo-prompt-framework/eval/synthesis.md`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_quality_card.md:\n  Line 8:   - \"mimo costar lean prompt\"\n\n  Line 41: OpenCode dispatches the MiniMax, MiMo, DeepSeek-v4-pro, and Kimi-K2.7 small models, which override or default against the cross-model defaults from the canonical card:\n\n  Line 47: | MiMo V2.5 Pro (Token Plan) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n\n  Line 48: | MiMo V2.5 Pro (Direct API) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n\n  Line 49: | MiMo V2.5 Pro UltraSpeed (Direct API, low-latency) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n\n  Line 50: | GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan) | COSTAR + lean (empirical, benchmark 008) | [`glm-5.2.md`](../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md) |\n\n  Line 53: **Executor notes:** Omit `--agent` for all small-model dispatches listed above. OpenCode maps `--variant low/medium/high` to MiMo's reasoning effort; `high` is the standing default for MiMo. MiniMax Token Plan (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`) and Direct API (`minimax/MiniMax-M3`) both serve M3. Xiaomi Token Plan (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`) and Direct API (`xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`) both serve MiMo-V2.5-Pro; the Direct API additionally serves `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, a low-latency tier with the same prompt contract. Ambiguous use-case (1 vs 2 vs 3) prevents the router from picking a path — resolve before dispatch. Always include a self-invocation guard signal when the dispatched session could loop back.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/README.md:\n  Line 121: Before the first dispatch in a session the skill runs `opencode providers list`. Seven providers are documented: `deepseek` (direct API, the default), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan, the default MiniMax path), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe), `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API), `kimi-for-coding` (Kimi For Coding plan; model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7`) and `openai` (paid premium). If the default `deepseek` is missing the skill asks before falling back, and it never substitutes a model you did not approve.\n\n  Line 193: A: Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` via the direct DeepSeek API, which gives elevated reasoning at low cost. Switch to `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` for the MiniMax Token Plan or `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` for MiMo through the Xiaomi Token Plan. Use `openai/gpt-5.5` for paid premium dispatches.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:\n  Line 25: <!-- Keywords: opencode, opencode-cli, opencode-run, cross-ai, spec-kit-runtime, plugin-runtime, parallel-sessions, share-url, detached-session, agent-delegation, deepseek, openai, minimax, minimax-coding-plan, minimax-m3, token-plan, xiaomi, xiaomi-token-plan, xiaomi-token-plan-ams, xiaomi-api, xiaomi-direct, mimo, mimo-v2.5-pro, mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed, ultraspeed, glm-5.2, zai-coding-plan, z.ai-coding-plan, glm-coding-plan -->\n\n  Line 198: **Authentication options**: `opencode providers login <provider>` (and `opencode auth login` for subscription plans) for OAuth and API key flows. Configured providers on a typical install: `deepseek` (api, DEFAULT), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan subscription — **DEFAULT MiniMax path**; `opencode auth login`; model `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API, pay-per-token — `opencode providers login minimax`; model `minimax/MiniMax-M3`), `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API, pay-per-token — `opencode providers login xiaomi`; models `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` and the low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe; `opencode auth login`; model `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead), `openai` (api, premium alternative for `gpt-5.5`/`gpt-5.5-pro`/`gpt-5.5-fast`).\n\n  Line 210: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\" && XIAOMI_OK=1       || XIAOMI_OK=0          # Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\n\n  Line 211: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"xiaomi([^-]|$)\"     && XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1 || XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0   # Xiaomi Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the token-plan-ams provider\n\n  Line 220: | Default missing, openai ready | 0 | 1 | **ASK user** before substituting to OpenAI — surface options A/B/C/D below; OpenAI is a paid premium fallback. |\n\n  Line 232: **MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n  Line 236: | MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (high reasoning is the standing default — opencode maps low/medium/high to MiMo's reasoning effort) — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13); confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n\n  Line 237: | MiMo speed variant requested (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive checks/smokes) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro serving tier, same COSTAR prompt contract as the standard model |\n\n  Line 238: | Direct API not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n\n  Line 239: | Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n\n  Line 242: **User prompt template — default missing, fallback configured:**\n\n  Line 246: A configured fallback is available. Pick one:\n\n  Line 248:   B) Use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API, configured now) — or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` for latency-sensitive runs\n\n  Line 261:   - `opencode auth login`                   (Xiaomi Token Plan — default Xiaomi path; pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\" → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams; model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro)\n\n  Line 262:   - `opencode providers login xiaomi`       (Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; models xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro and xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed)\n\n  Line 264:   - `opencode auth login`                   (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription; provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2)\n\n  Line 291: Run `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API); the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (omit `--agent`), the pay-per-token `minimax/MiniMax-M3` (Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo; high reasoning preset; omit `--agent`), `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo; pay-per-token) and `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (low-latency MiMo tier, same prompt contract) remain available. The Kimi For Coding plan model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (\"Kimi K2.7 Code\"; 256k / 262,144-token context; subscription billing — dispatch cost 0; omit `--agent`; `--variant high` accepted but effect benchmark-unverified) is the coding-optimized large-context Kimi path. **Operational caveat (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`. The Z.AI GLM Coding Plan model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (\"GLM-5.2\"; flagship long-horizon coding; 1,000,000-token context / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs; subscription billing; omit `--agent`; `--variant`↔`reasoning_effort` mapping unverified — GLM has native high/max, smoke-test before relying on it; thinking on by default + preserved on the Coding Plan endpoint) is the Z.AI direct-provider GLM path, superseding the gateway-only `glm-5.1` removed in v1.3.15.0; confirm the live slug via `opencode models zai-coding-plan`. **Operational (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45...\n  Line 293: Shared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n\n  Line 335: 3. Pin model + variant + format + dir explicitly — **no `--agent`** (see the Default Invocation note: current opencode rejects a top-level `--agent general`; put any agent-profile request in the prompt body). Default: `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root>`. Honor user overrides verbatim (e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`, `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, `minimax/MiniMax-M3`, `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, `openai/gpt-5.5-pro`).\n\n  Line 350: 15. **Destructive-scope-violation prevention (RM-8) for deep-loop dispatches** — If a permissions-matrix config is loaded (via `--permissions-matrix <path>` flag or recipe field), the structured gate applies and the four-layer prose mitigation is bypassed; see `references/permissions-matrix.md`. Without a loaded matrix, any non-interactive `opencode run` with `--dangerously-skip-permissions` against a populated worktree MUST apply the four-layer mitigation as a legacy fallback, deprecated-but-supported during transition: (L1) rendered prompt contains literal `BANNED OPERATIONS` and `ALLOWED WRITE PATHS`; (L2) `--dir` points at a fresh `git worktree`; (L3) main `git status` clean OR committed, recovery-baseline commit hash recorded; (L4) for multi-phase / phase-parent targets, prefer `cli-copilot` + `gpt-5.5 --reasoning-effort high` over `deepseek-v4-pro`. Background: on 2026-05-04 an `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` dispatch under `/deep:review:auto` deleted 44 files across two phase folders because the only safeguard was prose and `--dangerously-skip-permissions` granted unrestricted FS write. Full incident + root cause + checklist: `references/destructive_scope_violations.md`.\n\n  Line 351: 16. **Single-dispatch discipline (operator-gated, session-scoped)** — Default: launch ONE cli-* dispatch at a time across the cli-* family (cli-opencode, cli-claude-code). Wait for the dispatched agent's work to return, verify outputs exist, then SIGKILL the dispatcher process + any orphan children (`pkill -9 -f \"opencode run\"` for this skill, plus `gtimeout` / `positional_scoring_fallback:app` cleanup). Only launch the next dispatch (this skill OR a sibling) after the prior one is dead and RSS has dropped. **Within a deep-flow session** (deep-review / deep-research): the operator authorizes the whole multi-iteration session at start — iterations chain back-to-back with kill-between as the safety mechanism, NOT a per-iteration operator confirmation prompt. **Exception (cross-skill parallel)**: when the operator explicitly authorizes N parallel dispatches, run N concurrently — but still SIGKILL each as its work returns.\n\n  Line 398: - [prompt_quality_card.md](./assets/prompt_quality_card.md) - Executor-specific model overrides (MiniMax, MiMo); delegates shared framework table and CLEAR check to canonical card\n\n  Line 446: - **Gate 2**: Skill routing via the Skill Advisor Hook (or `skill_advisor.py` fallback)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.7.0.md:\n  Line 10: `assets/prompt_quality_card.md` was carrying duplicated content from the canonical sk-prompt card (framework table) and sk-prompt-models hub (MiniMax/MiMo override paragraphs). This release replaces that duplication with targeted cross-links, reducing the card from 96 to 37 LOC. SKILL.md gains an explicit 3-tier prompt-composition precedence rule so dispatchers know where to look at each tier.\n\n  Line 18: | `assets/prompt_quality_card.md` | Trimmed 96 → 37 LOC | Removed framework table (delegates to sk-prompt canonical card); replaced MiniMax/MiMo inline override paragraphs with a compact table cross-linking sk-prompt-models hub profiles |\n\n  Line 25: - Inline MiniMax and MiMo override paragraphs replaced with a two-row table: model slug → framework → hub profile link. No information lost; source of truth moved to sk-prompt-models where it is maintained.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/context-budget.md:\n  Line 54: Use `../../sk-prompt-models/assets/per_model_budgets.json` for budget defaults and `../../sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json` for model profiles, context windows, quota pools, and fallback metadata.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/agent_delegation.md:\n  Line 80: cli-opencode dispatches use the `--agent <slug>` flag. The flag loads the agent definition from `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` (project-local) or the user-level fallback. The dispatch shape pins model, variant, format, and working directory alongside the agent slug:\n\n  Line 384: | `unknown agent <slug>` | Slug not present in `.opencode/agents/` or user-level fallback | Run `opencode agent list` to enumerate, fix the slug, retry |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/destructive_scope_violations.md:\n  Line 174: - **Memory feedback**: `feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md`, `feedback_opencode_provider_fallback.md`, `feedback_cli_executor_only_when_requested.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.14.0.md:\n  Line 4: **Status**: Documentation update. Adds the Xiaomi Direct API provider (`xiaomi`) as a pay-per-token alternative to the Token Plan, and removes all MiniMax M2.7 references in favor of MiniMax-M3 as the sole model for both Token Plan and Direct API.\n\n  Line 12: 1. **Xiaomi Direct API** — The `xiaomi` provider is now documented as a pay-per-token alternative to `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Token Plan), mirroring how MiniMax has both `minimax-coding-plan` (Token Plan) and `minimax` (Direct API). Model: `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`. Auth: `opencode providers login xiaomi`.\n\n  Line 22: | `SKILL.md` | Updated | Keywords, auth options, pre-flight (`XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK`), MiMo routing table (4 rows), model selection, fallback templates — all updated for xiaomi API + M3 consolidation |\n\n  Line 23: | `references/cli_reference.md` | Updated | Pre-flight, MiMo routing table, login commands, model table, variant notes — xiaomi API added, M2.7 removed |\n\n  Line 24: | `assets/prompt_templates.md` | Updated | Template 14 (MiniMax): M2.7-highspeed → M3; Template 15 (MiMo): added Direct API invocation path |\n\n  Line 25: | `assets/prompt_quality_card.md` | Updated | Removed M2.7 fallback row, added xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro (Direct API) row, updated executor notes |\n\n  Line 26: | `graph-metadata.json` | Updated | Trigger phrases: removed `minimax-2.7`, `-highspeed` variants; added `xiaomi-api`, `xiaomi api`, `xiaomi direct`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` |\n\n  Line 30: - **Provider**: `xiaomi` (pay-per-token). Auth via `opencode providers login xiaomi`.\n\n  Line 31: - **Model**: `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` (same model as Token Plan, different billing).\n\n  Line 32: - **Pre-flight detection**: `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK` via `grep -qE \"xiaomi([^-]|$)\"` (skips `xiaomi-token-plan-ams`).\n\n  Line 33: - **Routing**: 4-row MiMo routing table — Token Plan (default), Token Plan missing, Direct API requested, Direct API missing.\n\n  Line 38: - All `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed` fallback references removed.\n\n  Line 49: - Confirm live model ids with `opencode models xiaomi` before dispatch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.0.md:\n  Line 20: | `SKILL.md` | Updated | Default invocation, provider auth pre-flight + decision tree (`OPENCODE_GO_OK` removed), model selection, ALWAYS rules 3/11, keywords, fallback templates — all switched to the deepseek default |\n\n  Line 21: | `references/cli_reference.md` | Updated | Pre-flight, decision tree, login commands, model table, variant table — opencode-go rows and gateway-only models (`glm-5.1`, `qwen3.6-plus`, `deepseek-v4-flash` gateway dup, `mimo-v2.5-free`) removed |\n\n  Line 23: | `assets/prompt_quality_card.md`, `assets/prompt_templates.md` | Updated | Removed the opencode-go small-model list entry and the free MiMo gateway path |\n\n  Line 30: - Same underlying model; the change is the routing provider and its billing pool. Fallbacks remain `openai`, `xiaomi`, `kimi-for-coding`, `minimax` (Token Plan and Direct API).\n\n  Line 46: - Gateway-only models that had no direct-provider equivalent (`glm-5.1`, `glm-5.2`, `qwen3.6-plus`) are no longer offered. `kimi-k2.6` is superseded by the direct `kimi-for-coding/k2p7`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md:\n  Line 167: ### Provider Auth Pre-Flight (smart fallback)\n\n  Line 177: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\" && XIAOMI_OK=1       || XIAOMI_OK=0          # Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\n\n  Line 178: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"xiaomi([^-]|$)\"     && XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1 || XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0   # Xiaomi Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the token-plan-ams provider\n\n  Line 179: echo \"default=$DEEPSEEK_OK minimax_token=$MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK minimax_direct=$MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK xiaomi=$XIAOMI_OK xiaomi_direct=$XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK\"\n\n  Line 196: **MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n  Line 200: | MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13). Confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n\n  Line 201: | MiMo speed variant (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro tier, same prompt contract |\n\n  Line 202: | Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n\n  Line 204: | Direct API explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` (pay-per-token; confirm live ids via `opencode models xiaomi`) |\n\n  Line 205: | Direct API requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n\n  Line 220: opencode auth login          # → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (Xiaomi Token Plan, Europe)\n\n  Line 223: opencode providers login xiaomi\n\n  Line 225: # Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription. Interactive: pick \"Z.AI Coding Plan\".\n\n  Line 226: opencode auth login          # → provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\n\n  Line 229: > Do not mix region endpoints (international `minimax.io` vs China `minimaxi.com`). Confirm live model ids with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan`. The Xiaomi endpoint is provider-managed (no documented base URL — do not invent one); confirm live model ids with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Token Plan) or `opencode models xiaomi` (Direct API).\n\n  Line 237: OpenCode resolves models through configured providers. The cli-opencode skill supports `deepseek` (default), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo, explicitly-selectable; NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead), and `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo: `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` + low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, pay-per-token) — confirmed against `opencode providers list` and `opencode models`. Run `opencode models [provider]` for the full live list on a given install.\n\n  Line 244: | `zai-coding-plan` | `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` | Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM-5.2 flagship long-horizon coding (1M context; subscription); omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models zai-coding-plan` |\n\n  Line 247: | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — MiMo-V2.5-Pro: 1M-token context, strongly agentic (1000+ tool calls), token-efficient; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` |\n\n  Line 248: | `xiaomi` | `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; MiMo-V2.5-Pro; confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n\n  Line 261: | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (mimo-v2.5-pro) | `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high); **always use `--variant high`** (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13) |\n\n  Line 262: | `zai-coding-plan` (glm-5.2) | GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it |\n\n  Line 271: `--agent <slug>` loads an agent definition from `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` (project-local) or the user-level fallback. The agent definition's frontmatter pins the model, tool permissions, and system prompt that shape the dispatch.\n\n  Line 329: The cli-opencode self-invocation guard probes this directory as the third-layer fallback signal (per ADR-001).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.0.0.md:\n  Line 19: New §3 subsection codifies the pre-dispatch auth check. One-shot bash pre-flight (`opencode providers list`) captures `OPENCODE_GO_OK` and `DEEPSEEK_OK` flags. A 3-state decision table (default-available / default-missing-fallback-ready / both-missing) governs routing. Two user-prompt templates (default-missing-with-fallback A/B/C menu; both-missing login-command menu) make the ASK-not-substitute contract explicit. Cache invalidation on auth-error mid-dispatch reruns the pre-flight before retry. ALWAYS rule 11 mandates the pre-flight before first dispatch; the Error Handling table now points `provider/model not found` and `401 Unauthorized` rows back to the pre-flight.\n\n  Line 63: 1. Migrate to the equivalent `opencode-go/<id>` (e.g. `opencode-go/glm-5.1`, `opencode-go/kimi-k2.6`) if the upstream model is available through the gateway.\n\n  Line 66: The Provider Auth Pre-Flight ALWAYS rule 11 mandates a one-shot `opencode providers list` check on session start. If the default isn't configured, the AI surfaces a 3-option menu (use configured fallback / log in to default / name a different model) instead of silently swapping. Operators expecting a silent fallback should explicitly approve option A in the prompt.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.6.0.md:\n  Line 1: # cli-opencode v1.3.6.0 — MiMo-V2.5-Pro research findings + empirical prompt-framework (COSTAR)\n\n  Line 4: **Status**: Documentation + registry addendum. Resolves the two items v1.3.5.0 left pending: MiMo-V2.5-Pro's capability metadata (research) and its best prompt framework (empirical benchmark). No default change — `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` stays the skill default.\n\n  Line 10: v1.3.5.0 registered MiMo-V2.5-Pro with `context_length` and the best prompt framework marked **pending** (126/003 research + 126/004 benchmark). This release lands both results from real evidence:\n\n  Line 12: - **126/003 research** (live web sources + opencode provider metadata + on-machine probe) confirmed MiMo-V2.5-Pro's real specs.\n\n  Line 13: - **126/004 benchmark** (10/10 real `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` dispatches across 5 frameworks × 2 fixtures) named the empirical prompt-framework winner.\n\n  Line 21: | `references/cli_reference.md` | Updated | §5 MiMo row use-case: 1M-token context, strongly agentic (1000+ tool calls), token-efficient |\n\n  Line 22: | `assets/prompt_templates.md` | Updated | § Template 15 → **COSTAR** scaffold (Context/Objective/Style=\"no preamble\"/Tone/Audience=\"automated consumer\"/Response) + lean-to-medium pre-planning; RACE fallback; do NOT use TIDD-EC/dense |\n\n  Line 23: | `assets/prompt_quality_card.md` | Updated | §3 per-model override: MiMo → **COSTAR default, RACE fallback**; records the MiMo ≠ MiniMax divergence |\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"mimo|MiMo|glm|GLM|xiaomi|zai-coding-plan|token-plan|fallback","time":{"start":1783487742231,"end":1783487742244}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052459e0b1e9bdef016a4ddcfe1e0c81918711ba1c4d42b557"}},"id":"prt_f402741160013QsEnEye7MRbbt","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f402702d4001mwmUsz8AwO4zF7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487742247,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_A7ydpT2kWFmQCj5wM3QV0C5D","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"glm-5\\.2|glm|mimo|mimo-v2\\.5-pro|xiaomi|zai-coding-plan|fallback","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json","include":"*.json"},"output":"Found 49 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:\n  Line 3:   \"description\": \"Shared small-model profile registry for cli-opencode dispatch. Each model declares one or more executor paths with their provider + quota_pool, so the fallback engine can route across pools when one is exhausted. Active small-model rotation: DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code (Kimi For Coding plan via provider `kimi-for-coding`), MiniMax-M3 (default via the MiniMax Token Plan provider `minimax-coding-plan`; pay-per-token Direct API via provider `minimax`), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via the Xiaomi Token Plan Europe provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` or Xiaomi Direct API provider `xiaomi`), GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan via provider `zai-coding-plan`). Optional unverified separate-pool stub: Claude Haiku.\",\n\n  Line 20:       \"fallback_target\": null,\n\n  Line 37:         \"fallback\": null,\n\n  Line 43:           \"fallback_score\": null,\n\n  Line 71:       \"fallback_target\": null,\n\n  Line 89:         \"dedicated Kimi For Coding subscription pool (`kimi-for-coding`), independent of minimax / xiaomi pools\",\n\n  Line 96:         \"single executor path (no fallback if the kimi-for-coding pool is exhausted)\",\n\n  Line 105:         \"fallback\": \"tidd-ec\",\n\n  Line 113:           \"fallback_score\": 1.0,\n\n  Line 114:           \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 6 samples/cell, throttled serial real kimi-for-coding/k2p7 dispatches. (The 4th fixture hard-roman-to-int was excluded - its run stalled under orchestration churn; the 3-fixture result is conclusive.) Unlike the saturated run 006, correctness SEPARATED here. Per-framework correctness (n=18): tidd-ec 1.0 = race 1.0 = costar 1.0 (perfect tier) > cidi 0.996 > rcaf 0.992. Trust verdict: TIE on correctness (the 3 perfect frameworks cannot be statistically separated, top-pair margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). The actionable signal: rcaf (the former convention default) is objectively the WEAKEST - it produced strict-validator code that missed adversarial cases - so it is retired/avoided for this model. Among the perfect tier, costar is primary for cross-evidence robustness (also MiMo's empirical winner, benchmark 004; favored by run 006's judge); tidd-ec is the most token-efficient (25 vs costar 70 median words) and is the fallback. This objectively refutes run 006's subjective gpt-5.5 judge, which had wrongly ranked rcaf/race highest.\",\n\n  Line 143:       \"fallback_target\": null,\n\n  Line 175:         \"fallback\": \"rcaf\",\n\n  Line 181:           \"fallback_score\": 0.742,\n\n  Line 190:       \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 197:           \"provider\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n\n  Line 198:           \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 200:           \"notes\": \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) via opencode provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (credential 'Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)'). Live slug xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro (confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13, 2026-06-01); verify the full live list with 'opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams'. Omit --agent (warns + falls back on 1.15.13). Manual direct-provider reroute uses xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined. Context window 1,000,000 tokens (released 2026-04-22). OpenAI-compatible endpoint https://token-plan-ams.xiaomimimo.com/v1; opencode cost shows 0/0 (Token-Plan subscription). --variant maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) in opencode settings — always dispatch with --variant high (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13). Best prompt framework (benchmark 004, 10/10 real runs): COSTAR or RACE + lean pre-planning — frame for format/brevity, not guardrails; TIDD-EC/dense ranked last; avoid CIDI (intermittent tool-only file-writes).\"\n\n  Line 203:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 204:       \"fallback_target\": null,\n\n  Line 207:         \"model_slug\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 212:         \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 214:         \"notes\": \"Live slug `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13 (2026-06-01). default_variant high: `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) and `--variant high` is confirmed accepted — always dispatch with it. agent_policy omit-general: `--agent` warns and falls back on 1.15.13. format_mode json: OpenAI-compatible endpoint; dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized envelope. Manual direct-provider reroutes use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined.\",\n\n  Line 223:         \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) subscription billing via provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n\n  Line 224:         \"separate quota pool (xiaomi-token-plan) independent of minimax / cognition pools\",\n\n  Line 225:         \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n\n  Line 231:         \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents — spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n\n  Line 237:         \"fallback\": \"race\",\n\n  Line 246:           \"fallback_score\": 0.9934,\n\n  Line 250:         \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md\",\n\n  Line 255:       \"id\": \"glm-5.2\",\n\n  Line 262:           \"provider\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n\n  Line 263:           \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n\n  Line 265:           \"notes\": \"Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (subscription) via opencode provider `zai-coding-plan` (auth credential 'Z.AI Coding Plan'). Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`; confirmed present via `opencode models zai-coding-plan` 2026-06-28 → glm-4.5-air/glm-4.7/glm-5-turbo/glm-5.1/glm-5.2/glm-5v-turbo. Flagship long-horizon coding model (supersedes the gateway-only glm-5.1 removed in cli-opencode v1.3.15.0). context_length 1,000,000 / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs — opencode `models` did not expose limits, re-verify. Omit `--agent` at top level. GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it. Thinking is on by default and the Coding Plan endpoint preserves thinking. Re-verify the live slug before automation — Z.AI ids drift (provider also serves glm-4.7 / glm-5.1 / glm-5-turbo).\"\n\n  Line 268:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n\n  Line 269:       \"fallback_target\": null,\n\n  Line 272:         \"model_slug\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n\n  Line 277:         \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n\n  Line 283:         \"vision\": \"native vision-to-code; image input via the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 image_url block at https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions) — opencode `--file` does NOT deliver images to this provider per upstream #20802; confirmed live 2026-06-28; see references/models/glm-5.2.md §7\",\n\n  Line 284:         \"notes\": \"Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` confirmed present 2026-06-28 (`opencode models zai-coding-plan`). agent_policy omit-general: do not pass `--agent` at the top level. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high + variant_status accepted-unverified: GLM's native `reasoning_effort` has high/max, but whether opencode `--variant high/max` forwards to it is not confirmed — smoke-test, do not depend on it. Subscription billing: confirm dispatch cost via smoke test. GLM dispatch quirks (Z.AI docs): thinking on by default + preserved thinking on the Coding Plan endpoint; function-calling `tool_choice` only `auto`; streaming tool calls need `tool_stream=true`. Re-verify slug before dispatch (Z.AI ids drift).\"\n\n  Line 287:         \"dedicated Z.AI GLM Coding Plan subscription pool (`zai-coding-plan`), independent of kimi / minimax / xiaomi pools\",\n\n  Line 294:         \"single executor path (no fallback if the zai-coding-plan pool is exhausted)\",\n\n  Line 305:         \"fallback\": \"tidd-ec\",\n\n  Line 311:           \"benchmark\": \"008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework\",\n\n  Line 313:           \"fallback_score\": 1.0,\n\n  Line 314:           \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 3 samples/cell, real zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 dispatches graded by the deterministic hidden-test oracle (grader noop, no LLM-judge bias). Run status SEPARABLE: per-framework correctness costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976 (the ONLY sub-perfect framework; also worst format adherence 0.889). Trust verdict TIE on correctness among the perfect tier (top-pair costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). costar is primary as best-of-tied: perfect correctness + tersest output (13 median words vs tidd-ec 38, cidi/race 94) + cross-model corroboration (also the empirical winner for kimi benchmark 007 and mimo benchmark 004). tidd-ec fallback (perfect, 2nd-tersest). rcaf avoided (only correctness misses + worst format). NOTE: CRAFT (the phase-1 doc-guided default) is NOT in the harness framework registry [rcaf,race,cidi,tidd-ec,costar] so it could not be benchmarked; the empirical winner among the 5 supported frameworks replaces it. 1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, excluded from scoring).\",\n\n  Line 317:         \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n\n  Line 332:           \"notes\": \"Future small-model fallback candidate. Adoption blocked until quota-pool semantics verified.\"\n\n  Line 336:       \"fallback_target\": null,\n\n  Line 341:         \"future fallback candidate\"\n","metadata":{"matches":49,"truncated":false},"title":"glm-5\\.2|glm|mimo|mimo-v2\\.5-pro|xiaomi|zai-coding-plan|fallback","time":{"start":1783487742229,"end":1783487742246}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052459e0b1e9bdef016a4ddcfe1e048191b2e7e551720af9d2"}},"id":"prt_f40274114001DYu4HN0cIdHdKr","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f402702d4001mwmUsz8AwO4zF7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487742249,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_RBknv8tcoyOdPJ4hZI0lfWbG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts","offset":261,"limit":190},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n261:   }\n262: }\n263: \n264: function assertMaxHops(edges: readonly FallbackEdge[], maxHops: number): void {\n265:   const adjacency = new Map<string, readonly string[]>();\n266:   for (const edge of edges) {\n267:     adjacency.set(edge.source.id, [...(adjacency.get(edge.source.id) ?? []), edge.targetId]);\n268:   }\n269: \n270:   function walk(sourceId: string, hopCount: number): void {\n271:     if (hopCount > maxHops) {\n272:       throw new Error(`fallback graph max-hop violation from ${sourceId}; allowed ${maxHops} hops`);\n273:     }\n274: \n275:     for (const targetId of adjacency.get(sourceId) ?? []) {\n276:       walk(targetId, hopCount + 1);\n277:     }\n278:   }\n279: \n280:   for (const sourceId of adjacency.keys()) {\n281:     walk(sourceId, 0);\n282:   }\n283: }\n284: \n285: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n286: // 3. CORE LOGIC\n287: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n288: \n289: /**\n290:  * Validate fallback graph edges before any dispatch uses them.\n291:  *\n292:  * Checks missing targets, cycles, cross-scope edges, and configured hop limits\n293:  * without mutating the registry.\n294:  *\n295:  * @param registry - The model registry with fallback configurations.\n296:  * @param options - Validation limits for graph traversal.\n297:  * @throws Error when the fallback graph is unsafe to dispatch.\n298:  */\n299: export function validateFallbackGraph(\n300:   registry: ModelRegistry,\n301:   options: FallbackGraphValidationOptions = {},\n302: ): void {\n303:   const edges = buildEdges(registry);\n304:   const maxHops = options.maxHops ?? DEFAULT_MAX_HOPS;\n305: \n306:   assertKnownTargets(registry, edges);\n307:   assertScopesDoNotWiden(registry, edges);\n308:   assertNoCycles(edges);\n309:   assertMaxHops(edges, maxHops);\n310: }\n311: \n312: /**\n313:  * Create a router after validating configured fallback edges.\n314:  *\n315:  * @param registry - The model registry with fallback configurations.\n316:  * @param options - Validation limits for graph traversal.\n317:  * @returns A router bound to the validated registry.\n318:  * @throws Error when the fallback graph is unsafe to dispatch.\n319:  */\n320: export function createFallbackRouter(\n321:   registry: ModelRegistry,\n322:   options: FallbackGraphValidationOptions = {},\n323: ): FallbackRouter {\n324:   validateFallbackGraph(registry, options);\n325: \n326:   return {\n327:     resolve(\n328:       failedModelId: string,\n329:       approvedModelIds?: readonly string[],\n330:       context?: FallbackRouteContext,\n331:     ): FallbackRoute {\n332:       return resolveFallback(failedModelId, registry, approvedModelIds, context);\n333:     },\n334:   };\n335: }\n336: \n337: /**\n338:  * Resolve the fallback route when a model exhausts its quota pool.\n339:  *\n340:  * Checks whether the failed model has a configured fallback target in a\n341:  * different quota pool and returns the appropriate route.\n342:  *\n343:  * The optional approval set closes the substitution gap: routing only ever\n344:  * resolves to a model the caller approved. The configured `fallback_target` is\n345:  * the approved route by definition, so the guard rejects only a target the\n346:  * caller never sanctioned, and never the legitimate cross-pool fallback. When\n347:  * the set is omitted, the configured target is treated as approved (existing\n348:  * behavior), so this is additive.\n349:  *\n350:  * @param failedModelId - The model ID that failed.\n351:  * @param registry - The model registry with fallback configurations.\n352:  * @param approvedModelIds - Optional set of model IDs the caller approved; when\n353:  *   provided, a target outside the set returns fail-fast instead of routing.\n354:  * @param context - Optional typed route context for failure kind and trace data.\n355:  * @returns A route indicating whether to fallback or fail-fast, with a reason.\n356:  */\n357: export function resolveFallback(\n358:   failedModelId: string,\n359:   registry: ModelRegistry,\n360:   approvedModelIds?: readonly string[],\n361:   context?: FallbackRouteContext,\n362: ): FallbackRoute {\n363:   const trace = createTrace(failedModelId, context);\n364:   const failedModel = findModel(registry, failedModelId);\n365:   if (failedModel === undefined) {\n366:     return withRouteMetadata(\n367:       {\n368:         action: 'fail-fast',\n369:         reason: `unknown model ${failedModelId}; no quota pool available for fallback routing`,\n370:       },\n371:       trace,\n372:       context?.failureKind,\n373:     );\n374:   }\n375: \n376:   const selection = selectTarget(failedModel, context);\n377:   if (selection.target === null) {\n378:     return withRouteMetadata(\n379:       {\n380:         action: 'fail-fast',\n381:         reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured for ${failedModel.id}`,\n382:       },\n383:       trace,\n384:       selection.failureKind,\n385:     );\n386:   }\n387: \n388:   const targetModel = findModel(registry, selection.target);\n389:   if (targetModel === undefined) {\n390:     return withRouteMetadata(\n391:       {\n392:         action: 'fail-fast',\n393:         reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, configured ${describeTargetKind(selection)} ${selection.target} is not in the registry`,\n394:       },\n395:       trace,\n396:       selection.failureKind,\n397:     );\n398:   }\n399: \n400:   if (targetModel.quota_pool === failedModel.quota_pool) {\n401:     return withRouteMetadata(\n402:       {\n403:         action: 'fail-fast',\n404:         reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, fallback target ${targetModel.id} shares the same pool; same-pool fallback rejected`,\n405:       },\n406:       trace,\n407:       selection.failureKind,\n408:     );\n409:   }\n410: \n411:   if (approvedModelIds !== undefined && !approvedModelIds.includes(targetModel.id)) {\n412:     return withRouteMetadata(\n413:       {\n414:         action: 'fail-fast',\n415:         reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, fallback target ${targetModel.id} is not in the caller-approved model set; unapproved substitution rejected`,\n416:       },\n417:       trace,\n418:       selection.failureKind,\n419:     );\n420:   }\n421: \n422:   return withRouteMetadata(\n423:     {\n424:       action: 'fallback',\n425:       target: targetModel.id,\n426:       reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, routing ${failedModel.id} to separate ${targetModel.quota_pool} pool target ${targetModel.id}`,\n427:     },\n428:     trace,\n429:     selection.failureKind,\n430:   );\n431: }\n\n(End of file - total 431 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  }\n}\n\nfunction assertMaxHops(edges: readonly FallbackEdge[], maxHops: number): void {\n  const adjacency = new Map<string, readonly string[]>();\n  for (const edge of edges) {\n    adjacency.set(edge.source.id, [...(adjacency.get(edge.source.id) ?? []), edge.targetId]);\n  }\n\n  function walk(sourceId: string, hopCount: number): void {\n    if (hopCount > maxHops) {\n      throw new Error(`fallback graph max-hop violation from ${sourceId}; allowed ${maxHops} hops`);\n    }\n\n    for (const targetId of adjacency.get(sourceId) ?? []) {\n      walk(targetId, hopCount + 1);\n    }\n  }\n\n  for (const sourceId of adjacency.keys()) {","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts","text":"  }\n}\n\nfunction assertMaxHops(edges: readonly FallbackEdge[], maxHops: number): void {\n  const adjacency = new Map<string, readonly string[]>();\n  for (const edge of edges) {\n    adjacency.set(edge.source.id, [...(adjacency.get(edge.source.id) ?? []), edge.targetId]);\n  }\n\n  function walk(sourceId: string, hopCount: number): void {\n    if (hopCount > maxHops) {\n      throw new Error(`fallback graph max-hop violation from ${sourceId}; allowed ${maxHops} hops`);\n    }\n\n    for (const targetId of adjacency.get(sourceId) ?? []) {\n      walk(targetId, hopCount + 1);\n    }\n  }\n\n  for (const sourceId of adjacency.keys()) {\n    walk(sourceId, 0);\n  }\n}\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. CORE LOGIC\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Validate fallback graph edges before any dispatch uses them.\n *\n * Checks missing targets, cycles, cross-scope edges, and configured hop limits\n * without mutating the registry.\n *\n * @param registry - The model registry with fallback configurations.\n * @param options - Validation limits for graph traversal.\n * @throws Error when the fallback graph is unsafe to dispatch.\n */\nexport function validateFallbackGraph(\n  registry: ModelRegistry,\n  options: FallbackGraphValidationOptions = {},\n): void {\n  const edges = buildEdges(registry);\n  const maxHops = options.maxHops ?? DEFAULT_MAX_HOPS;\n\n  assertKnownTargets(registry, edges);\n  assertScopesDoNotWiden(registry, edges);\n  assertNoCycles(edges);\n  assertMaxHops(edges, maxHops);\n}\n\n/**\n * Create a router after validating configured fallback edges.\n *\n * @param registry - The model registry with fallback configurations.\n * @param options - Validation limits for graph traversal.\n * @returns A router bound to the validated registry.\n * @throws Error when the fallback graph is unsafe to dispatch.\n */\nexport function createFallbackRouter(\n  registry: ModelRegistry,\n  options: FallbackGraphValidationOptions = {},\n): FallbackRouter {\n  validateFallbackGraph(registry, options);\n\n  return {\n    resolve(\n      failedModelId: string,\n      approvedModelIds?: readonly string[],\n      context?: FallbackRouteContext,\n    ): FallbackRoute {\n      return resolveFallback(failedModelId, registry, approvedModelIds, context);\n    },\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Resolve the fallback route when a model exhausts its quota pool.\n *\n * Checks whether the failed model has a configured fallback target in a\n * different quota pool and returns the appropriate route.\n *\n * The optional approval set closes the substitution gap: routing only ever\n * resolves to a model the caller approved. The configured `fallback_target` is\n * the approved route by definition, so the guard rejects only a target the\n * caller never sanctioned, and never the legitimate cross-pool fallback. When\n * the set is omitted, the configured target is treated as approved (existing\n * behavior), so this is additive.\n *\n * @param failedModelId - The model ID that failed.\n * @param registry - The model registry with fallback configurations.\n * @param approvedModelIds - Optional set of model IDs the caller approved; when\n *   provided, a target outside the set returns fail-fast instead of routing.\n * @param context - Optional typed route context for failure kind and trace data.\n * @returns A route indicating whether to fallback or fail-fast, with a reason.\n */\nexport function resolveFallback(\n  failedModelId: string,\n  registry: ModelRegistry,\n  approvedModelIds?: readonly string[],\n  context?: FallbackRouteContext,\n): FallbackRoute {\n  const trace = createTrace(failedModelId, context);\n  const failedModel = findModel(registry, failedModelId);\n  if (failedModel === undefined) {\n    return withRouteMetadata(\n      {\n        action: 'fail-fast',\n        reason: `unknown model ${failedModelId}; no quota pool available for fallback routing`,\n      },\n      trace,\n      context?.failureKind,\n    );\n  }\n\n  const selection = selectTarget(failedModel, context);\n  if (selection.target === null) {\n    return withRouteMetadata(\n      {\n        action: 'fail-fast',\n        reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured for ${failedModel.id}`,\n      },\n      trace,\n      selection.failureKind,\n    );\n  }\n\n  const targetModel = findModel(registry, selection.target);\n  if (targetModel === undefined) {\n    return withRouteMetadata(\n      {\n        action: 'fail-fast',\n        reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, configured ${describeTargetKind(selection)} ${selection.target} is not in the registry`,\n      },\n      trace,\n      selection.failureKind,\n    );\n  }\n\n  if (targetModel.quota_pool === failedModel.quota_pool) {\n    return withRouteMetadata(\n      {\n        action: 'fail-fast',\n        reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, fallback target ${targetModel.id} shares the same pool; same-pool fallback rejected`,\n      },\n      trace,\n      selection.failureKind,\n    );\n  }\n\n  if (approvedModelIds !== undefined && !approvedModelIds.includes(targetModel.id)) {\n    return withRouteMetadata(\n      {\n        action: 'fail-fast',\n        reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, fallback target ${targetModel.id} is not in the caller-approved model set; unapproved substitution rejected`,\n      },\n      trace,\n      selection.failureKind,\n    );\n  }\n\n  return withRouteMetadata(\n    {\n      action: 'fallback',\n      target: targetModel.id,\n      reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, routing ${failedModel.id} to separate ${targetModel.quota_pool} pool target ${targetModel.id}`,\n    },\n    trace,\n    selection.failureKind,\n  );\n}","lineStart":261,"lineEnd":431,"totalLines":431,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts","time":{"start":1783487742238,"end":1783487742248}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052459e0b1e9bdef016a4ddcfe1e108191b2980004c7137293"}},"id":"prt_f40274117001Cc3bAW4FcafFNh","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f402702d4001mwmUsz8AwO4zF7"}}
