 OpenAI-compatible endpoint; dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized envelope. Manual direct-provider reroutes use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined.\",\n        \"modalities\": [\n          \"text\"\n        ]\n      },\n      \"strengths\": [\n        \"1,000,000-token context window (largest in the small-model rotation)\",\n        \"strongly agentic — sustains 1000+ sequential tool calls (SWE-bench Pro 57.2)\",\n        \"token-efficient — 40-60% fewer tokens/trajectory vs frontier models (Opus 4.6 / GPT-5.4)\",\n        \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) subscription billing via provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n        \"separate quota pool (xiaomi-token-plan) independent of minimax / cognition pools\",\n        \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n      ],\n      \"weaknesses\": [\n        \"long-context quality degrades past ~512k despite the 1M window\",\n        \"Token-Plan subscription request-window semantics unverified\",\n        \"prompt-framework benchmark 004 used 2 fixtures / single-sample — COSTAR vs RACE tie is within noise\",\n        \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents — spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n      ],\n      \"avg_iter_wall_clock_min\": null,\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"recommended_frameworks\": {\n        \"primary\": \"costar\",\n        \"fallback\": \"race\",\n        \"avoid\": [\n          \"tidd-ec\",\n          \"cidi\"\n        ],\n        \"preplanning_density\": \"lean\",\n        \"evidence\": {\n          \"benchmark\": \"004\",\n          \"primary_score\": 1.0,\n          \"fallback_score\": 0.9934,\n          \"sample\": \"10/10 real MiMo-V2.5-Pro runs at --variant high\",\n          \"confidence\": \"high\"\n        },\n        \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md\",\n        \"status\": \"empirical\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"glm-5.2\",\n      \"context_length\": 1000000,\n      \"tool_calling\": \"native\",\n      \"chat_template\": \"default\",\n      \"executors\": [\n        {\n          \"executor\": \"cli-opencode\",\n          \"provider\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n          \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n          \"status\": \"active\",\n          \"notes\": \"Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (subscription) via opencode provider `zai-coding-plan` (auth credential 'Z.AI Coding Plan'). Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`; confirmed present via `opencode models zai-coding-plan` 2026-06-28 → glm-4.5-air/glm-4.7/glm-5-turbo/glm-5.1/glm-5.2/glm-5v-turbo. Flagship long-horizon coding model (supersedes the gateway-only glm-5.1 removed in cli-opencode v1.3.15.0). context_length 1,000,000 / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs — opencode `models` did not expose limits, re-verify. Omit `--agent` at top level. GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it. Thinking is on by default and the Coding Plan endpoint preserves thinking. Re-verify the live slug before automation — Z.AI ids drift (provider also serves glm-4.7 / glm-5.1 / glm-5-turbo).\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n      \"fallback_target\": null,\n      \"free_tier\": false,\n      \"capability\": {\n        \"model_slug\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n        \"default_variant\": \"high\",\n        \"variant_flag\": \"--variant\",\n        \"agent_policy\": \"omit-general\",\n        \"format_mode\": \"json\",\n        \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n        \"variant_status\": \"accepted-unverified\",\n        \"modalities\": [\n          \"text\",\n          \"image\"\n        ],\n        \"vision\": \"native vision-to-code; image input via the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 image_url block at https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions) — opencode `--file` does NOT deliver images to this provider per upstream #20802; confirmed live 2026-06-28; see references/models/glm-5.2.md §7\",\n        \"notes\": \"Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` confirmed present 2026-06-28 (`opencode models zai-coding-plan`). agent_policy omit-general: do not pass `--agent` at the top level. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high + variant_status accepted-unverified: GLM's native `reasoning_effort` has high/max, but whether opencode `--variant high/max` forwards to it is not confirmed — smoke-test, do not depend on it. Subscription billing: confirm dispatch cost via smoke test. GLM dispatch quirks (Z.AI docs): thinking on by default + preserved thinking on the Coding Plan endpoint; function-calling `tool_choice` only `auto`; streaming tool calls need `tool_stream=true`. Re-verify slug before dispatch (Z.AI ids drift).\"\n      },\n      \"strengths\": [\n        \"dedicated Z.AI GLM Coding Plan subscription pool (`zai-coding-plan`), independent of kimi / minimax / xiaomi pools\",\n        \"flagship long-horizon coding model (Z.AI docs: Terminal-Bench 2.1 81.0, SWE-bench Pro 62.1 — both above GLM-5.1)\",\n        \"1,000,000-token context for long-file and multi-repo work (128K max output)\",\n        \"subscription billing via the Z.AI Coding Plan\",\n        \"native reasoning_effort (high/max) + thinking-by-default for complex multi-constraint coding\"\n      ],\n      \"weaknesses\": [\n        \"single executor path (no fallback if the zai-coding-plan pool is exhausted)\",\n        \"context_length / max-output recorded from Z.AI docs (1,000,000 / 131,072) — opencode `models` did not expose limits; re-verify on the install\",\n        \"--variant ↔ reasoning_effort mapping unverified (GLM has native high/max; opencode forwarding not confirmed)\",\n        \"best prompt framework is a TIE among the perfect tier (costar=tidd-ec=cidi=race at correctness 1.0); costar is best-of-tied (tersest + cross-model corroborated), not a decisive single winner — benchmark 008\",\n        \"thinking-on-by-default drives high latency variance — 6-161s observed over benchmark 008's 45 small code-gen cells (avg ~26s, ~27x spread); budget generous timeouts, a tight timeout kills the slow tail\",\n        \"~1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, dispatch_failed) in benchmark 008 — expect occasional transient dispatch failures at scale; retry the cell rather than treating it as a model error\"\n      ],\n      \"avg_iter_wall_clock_min\": null,\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"recommended_frameworks\": {\n        \"primary\": \"costar\",\n        \"fallback\": \"tidd-ec\",\n        \"avoid\": [\n          \"rcaf\"\n        ],\n        \"preplanning_density\": \"lean\",\n        \"evidence\": {\n          \"benchmark\": \"008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework\",\n          \"primary_score\": 1.0,\n          \"fallback_score\": 1.0,\n          \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 3 samples/cell, real zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 dispatches graded by the deterministic hidden-test oracle (grader noop, no LLM-judge bias). Run status SEPARABLE: per-framework correctness costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976 (the ONLY sub-perfect framework; also worst format adherence 0.889). Trust verdict TIE on correctness among the perfect tier (top-pair costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). costar is primary as best-of-tied: perfect correctness + tersest output (13 median words vs tidd-ec 38, cidi/race 94) + cross-model corroboration (also the empirical winner for kimi benchmark 007 and mimo benchmark 004). tidd-ec fallback (perfect, 2nd-tersest). rcaf avoided (only correctness misses + worst format). NOTE: CRAFT (the phase-1 doc-guided default) is NOT in the harness framework registry [rcaf,race,cidi,tidd-ec,costar] so it could not be benchmarked; the empirical winner among the 5 supported frameworks replaces it. 1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, excluded from scoring).\",\n          \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n        },\n        \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n        \"status\": \"empirical\"\n      }","lineStart":180,"lineEnd":319,"totalLines":352,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json","time":{"start":1783487753780,"end":1783487753788}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_034eae1d9ad04063016a4ddd09a8dc81918f04da496b39e3a5"}},"id":"prt_f40276df6001s1aYKVY86vXDoz","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f402743fe001CeJrohyUww48Fw"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487753790,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Eq2F92xGboUo9u3AClOQBrIz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md","offset":196,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n196: **MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n197: \n198: | State | Condition | Action |\n199: |-------|-----------|--------|\n200: | MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13). Confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n201: | MiMo speed variant (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro tier, same prompt contract |\n202: | Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n203: | Token Plan not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n204: | Direct API explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` (pay-per-token; confirm live ids via `opencode models xiaomi`) |\n205: | Direct API requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n206: \n207: **Login / setup command shapes** (the AI surfaces these to the user; the user runs them in their own terminal):\n208: \n209: ```bash\n210: # Recommended default — direct DeepSeek API\n211: opencode providers login deepseek\n212: \n213: # MiniMax Token Plan — DEFAULT MiniMax path (subscription). Interactive: pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\".\n214: opencode auth login          # → provider minimax-coding-plan; Anthropic-compatible https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1 (China: api.minimaxi.com)\n215: \n216: # MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative (needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; platform endpoint https://api.minimax.io/v1)\n217: opencode providers login minimax\n218: \n219: # Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — provider-managed endpoint. Interactive: pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\".\n220: opencode auth login          # → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (Xiaomi Token Plan, Europe)\n221: \n222: # Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token alternative\n223: opencode providers login xiaomi\n224: \n225: # Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription. Interactive: pick \"Z.AI Coding Plan\".\n226: opencode auth login          # → provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\n227: ```\n228: \n229: > Do not mix region endpoints (international `minimax.io` vs China `minimaxi.com`). Confirm live model ids with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan`. The Xiaomi endpoint is provider-managed (no documented base URL — do not invent one); confirm live model ids with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Token Plan) or `opencode models xiaomi` (Direct API).\n230: \n231: **On auth-error mid-dispatch** (`401 Unauthorized`, `provider/model not found`): invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## 5. MODEL SELECTION\n236: \n237: OpenCode resolves models through configured providers. The cli-opencode skill supports `deepseek` (default), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo, explicitly-selectable; NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead), and `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo: `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` + low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, pay-per-token) — confirmed against `opencode providers list` and `opencode models`. Run `opencode models [provider]` for the full live list on a given install.\n238: \n239: | Provider | Example model id | Use case |\n240: |----------|------------------|----------|\n241: | `deepseek` (DEFAULT) | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` | Default — deep reasoning at low cost via direct DeepSeek API |\n242: | `deepseek` | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` | Latency-optimized direct-API sibling |\n243: | `kimi-for-coding` | `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` | Long-context Kimi K2.7 Code (256k; subscription plan) |\n244: | `zai-coding-plan` | `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` | Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM-5.2 flagship long-horizon coding (1M context; subscription); omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models zai-coding-plan` |\n245: | `minimax-coding-plan` (DEFAULT MiniMax) | `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` | MiniMax Token Plan (subscription) — default MiniMax dispatch; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan` |\n246: | `minimax` | `minimax/MiniMax-M3` | MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative; needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax` |\n247: | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — MiMo-V2.5-Pro: 1M-token context, strongly agentic (1000+ tool calls), token-efficient; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` |\n248: | `xiaomi` | `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; MiMo-V2.5-Pro; confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n249: \n250: `opencode models <provider>` lists every model id the provider exposes. The model string passed to `--model` is always `provider/model-id`.\n251: \n252: ### Reasoning effort via `--variant`\n253: \n254: The `--variant` flag maps to provider-specific reasoning effort. Underlying-model conventions apply per provider routing.\n255: \n256: | Provider | Variant values |\n257: |----------|----------------|\n258: | `deepseek` (`deepseek-v4-pro`) | reasoning effort accepted |\n259: | `deepseek` (`deepseek-v4-flash`) | non-reasoning — `--variant` ignored |\n260: | `minimax-coding-plan` / `minimax` (MiniMax-M3) | `--variant` behavior unverified — omitted by default; confirm against the MiniMax API before relying on it |\n261: | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (mimo-v2.5-pro) | `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high); **always use `--variant high`** (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13) |\n262: | `zai-coding-plan` (glm-5.2) | GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it |\n263: | `openai` (`gpt-5.5` / `gpt-5.5-fast` / `gpt-5.5-pro`) | `--variant` maps to OpenAI reasoning effort: `none`/`low`/`medium`/`high`/**`xhigh`** (`gpt-5.5-pro`: `medium`/`high`/`xhigh`). **`openai/gpt-5.5-fast`** is the low-latency **Fast** variant (OpenAI `priority` service tier) with the same effort range — e.g. `--model openai/gpt-5.5-fast --variant xhigh`. The cache lists it as `gpt-5.5` + `experimental.modes:['fast']`, but `opencode models openai` resolves the `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` slug directly. |\n264: \n265: Default skill behavior: pass `--variant high` for cross-AI dispatches. Operators may override via the prompt template's variant field.\n\n(Showing lines 196-265 of 379. Use offset=266 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"**MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13). Confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n| MiMo speed variant (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro tier, same prompt contract |\n| Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n| Token Plan not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n| Direct API explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` (pay-per-token; confirm live ids via `opencode models xiaomi`) |\n| Direct API requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n\n**Login / setup command shapes** (the AI surfaces these to the user; the user runs them in their own terminal):\n\n```bash\n# Recommended default — direct DeepSeek API\nopencode providers login deepseek\n\n# MiniMax Token Plan — DEFAULT MiniMax path (subscription). Interactive: pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\".\nopencode auth login          # → provider minimax-coding-plan; Anthropic-compatible https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1 (China: api.minimaxi.com)\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md","text":"**MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13). Confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n| MiMo speed variant (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro tier, same prompt contract |\n| Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n| Token Plan not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n| Direct API explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` (pay-per-token; confirm live ids via `opencode models xiaomi`) |\n| Direct API requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n\n**Login / setup command shapes** (the AI surfaces these to the user; the user runs them in their own terminal):\n\n```bash\n# Recommended default — direct DeepSeek API\nopencode providers login deepseek\n\n# MiniMax Token Plan — DEFAULT MiniMax path (subscription). Interactive: pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\".\nopencode auth login          # → provider minimax-coding-plan; Anthropic-compatible https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1 (China: api.minimaxi.com)\n\n# MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative (needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; platform endpoint https://api.minimax.io/v1)\nopencode providers login minimax\n\n# Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — provider-managed endpoint. Interactive: pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\".\nopencode auth login          # → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (Xiaomi Token Plan, Europe)\n\n# Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token alternative\nopencode providers login xiaomi\n\n# Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription. Interactive: pick \"Z.AI Coding Plan\".\nopencode auth login          # → provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\n```\n\n> Do not mix region endpoints (international `minimax.io` vs China `minimaxi.com`). Confirm live model ids with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan`. The Xiaomi endpoint is provider-managed (no documented base URL — do not invent one); confirm live model ids with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Token Plan) or `opencode models xiaomi` (Direct API).\n\n**On auth-error mid-dispatch** (`401 Unauthorized`, `provider/model not found`): invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n\n---\n\n## 5. MODEL SELECTION\n\nOpenCode resolves models through configured providers. The cli-opencode skill supports `deepseek` (default), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo, explicitly-selectable; NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead), and `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo: `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` + low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, pay-per-token) — confirmed against `opencode providers list` and `opencode models`. Run `opencode models [provider]` for the full live list on a given install.\n\n| Provider | Example model id | Use case |\n|----------|------------------|----------|\n| `deepseek` (DEFAULT) | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` | Default — deep reasoning at low cost via direct DeepSeek API |\n| `deepseek` | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` | Latency-optimized direct-API sibling |\n| `kimi-for-coding` | `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` | Long-context Kimi K2.7 Code (256k; subscription plan) |\n| `zai-coding-plan` | `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` | Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM-5.2 flagship long-horizon coding (1M context; subscription); omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models zai-coding-plan` |\n| `minimax-coding-plan` (DEFAULT MiniMax) | `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` | MiniMax Token Plan (subscription) — default MiniMax dispatch; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan` |\n| `minimax` | `minimax/MiniMax-M3` | MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative; needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax` |\n| `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — MiMo-V2.5-Pro: 1M-token context, strongly agentic (1000+ tool calls), token-efficient; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` |\n| `xiaomi` | `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; MiMo-V2.5-Pro; confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n\n`opencode models <provider>` lists every model id the provider exposes. The model string passed to `--model` is always `provider/model-id`.\n\n### Reasoning effort via `--variant`\n\nThe `--variant` flag maps to provider-specific reasoning effort. Underlying-model conventions apply per provider routing.\n\n| Provider | Variant values |\n|----------|----------------|\n| `deepseek` (`deepseek-v4-pro`) | reasoning effort accepted |\n| `deepseek` (`deepseek-v4-flash`) | non-reasoning — `--variant` ignored |\n| `minimax-coding-plan` / `minimax` (MiniMax-M3) | `--variant` behavior unverified — omitted by default; confirm against the MiniMax API before relying on it |\n| `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (mimo-v2.5-pro) | `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high); **always use `--variant high`** (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13) |\n| `zai-coding-plan` (glm-5.2) | GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it |\n| `openai` (`gpt-5.5` / `gpt-5.5-fast` / `gpt-5.5-pro`) | `--variant` maps to OpenAI reasoning effort: `none`/`low`/`medium`/`high`/**`xhigh`** (`gpt-5.5-pro`: `medium`/`high`/`xhigh`). **`openai/gpt-5.5-fast`** is the low-latency **Fast** variant (OpenAI `priority` service tier) with the same effort range — e.g. `--model openai/gpt-5.5-fast --variant xhigh`. The cache lists it as `gpt-5.5` + `experimental.modes:['fast']`, but `opencode models openai` resolves the `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` slug directly. |\n\nDefault skill behavior: pass `--variant high` for cross-AI dispatches. Operators may override via the prompt template's variant field.","lineStart":196,"lineEnd":265,"totalLines":379,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md","time":{"start":1783487753784,"end":1783487753789}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_034eae1d9ad04063016a4ddd09a8e48191966eb2ac20446b2c"}},"id":"prt_f40276e36001Oz2CIXOxBE2R2V","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f402743fe001CeJrohyUww48Fw"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487753829,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kFsqD6A2esvYZtB3f6lHZQVD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts","offset":1,"limit":110},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Registry ↔ Advisor Routing Drift Guard\n3: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: //\n5: import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n6: import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n7: import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n8: import { dirname, resolve } from 'node:path';\n9: import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n10: \n11: import { describe, expect, it } from 'vitest';\n12: \n13: import { findAdvisorWorkspaceRoot } from '../lib/utils/workspace-root.js';\n14: import {\n15:   DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL,\n16:   DEEP_ROUTING_PROJECTION_HASH,\n17:   SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS,\n18: } from '../lib/scorer/aliases.js';\n19: \n20: const here = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n21: const repoRoot = findAdvisorWorkspaceRoot(here);\n22: const advisorScript = resolve(\n23:   repoRoot,\n24:   '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py',\n25: );\n26: const registryPath = resolve(repoRoot, '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json');\n27: \n28: type RoutingClass = 'lexical' | 'alias-fold' | 'metadata' | 'command-bridge';\n29: \n30: interface AdvisorRouting {\n31:   readonly routingClass: RoutingClass;\n32:   readonly legacyAdvisorId?: string;\n33:   readonly advisorDefaultMode?: boolean;\n34:   readonly legacyAliases?: readonly string[];\n35:   readonly packetSkillName: string;\n36: }\n37: interface Mode {\n38:   readonly workflowMode: string;\n39:   readonly packet: string;\n40:   readonly advisorRouting: AdvisorRouting;\n41: }\n42: interface ProjectionEntry {\n43:   readonly legacyAdvisorId: string;\n44:   readonly workflowMode: string;\n45:   readonly routingClass: 'lexical' | 'alias-fold';\n46:   readonly advisorDefaultMode: boolean;\n47:   readonly legacyAliases: readonly string[];\n48: }\n49: interface RoutingDump {\n50:   readonly DEEP_ROUTING_PROJECTION_HASH: string;\n51:   readonly DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS: string[];\n52:   readonly DEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY: Record<string, string>;\n53:   readonly PY_ALIAS_GROUP_KEYS: string[];\n54: }\n55: const registry = JSON.parse(readFileSync(registryPath, 'utf8')) as { modes: readonly Mode[] };\n56: \n57: function registryProjectionEntries(classes: readonly RoutingClass[]): ProjectionEntry[] {\n58:   const entries: ProjectionEntry[] = [];\n59:   for (const mode of registry.modes) {\n60:     const ar = mode.advisorRouting;\n61:     if ((ar.routingClass === 'lexical' || ar.routingClass === 'alias-fold') && classes.includes(ar.routingClass)) {\n62:       entries.push({\n63:         legacyAdvisorId: ar.legacyAdvisorId as string,\n64:         workflowMode: mode.workflowMode,\n65:         routingClass: ar.routingClass,\n66:         advisorDefaultMode: ar.advisorDefaultMode === true,\n67:         legacyAliases: [...(ar.legacyAliases ?? [])],\n68:       });\n69:     }\n70:   }\n71:   return entries.sort((left, right) => left.legacyAdvisorId.localeCompare(right.legacyAdvisorId));\n72: }\n73: \n74: function projectionHash(entries: readonly ProjectionEntry[]): string {\n75:   const canonical = JSON.stringify({\n76:     skill: 'deep-loop-workflows',\n77:     entries: entries.map((entry) => ({\n78:       legacyAdvisorId: entry.legacyAdvisorId,\n79:       workflowMode: entry.workflowMode,\n80:       routingClass: entry.routingClass,\n81:       advisorDefaultMode: entry.advisorDefaultMode,\n82:       legacyAliases: [...entry.legacyAliases],\n83:     })),\n84:   });\n85:   return `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(canonical).digest('hex')}`;\n86: }\n87: \n88: function generatedTypeScriptProjectionEntries(): ProjectionEntry[] {\n89:   const registryById = new Map(\n90:     registryProjectionEntries(['lexical', 'alias-fold'])\n91:       .map((entry) => [entry.legacyAdvisorId, entry] as const),\n92:   );\n93:   return Object.entries(DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL)\n94:     .map(([legacyAdvisorId, workflowMode]) => {\n95:       const registryEntry = registryById.get(legacyAdvisorId);\n96:       expect(registryEntry, `registry entry missing for ${legacyAdvisorId}`).toBeDefined();\n97:       return {\n98:         legacyAdvisorId,\n99:         workflowMode,\n100:         routingClass: registryEntry!.routingClass,\n101:         advisorDefaultMode: registryEntry!.advisorDefaultMode,\n102:         legacyAliases: [...(SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS[legacyAdvisorId] ?? [])],\n103:       };\n104:     })\n105:     .sort((left, right) => left.legacyAdvisorId.localeCompare(right.legacyAdvisorId));\n106: }\n107: \n108: function generatedPythonProjectionEntries(dump: RoutingDump): ProjectionEntry[] {\n109:   const registryById = new Map(\n110:     registryProjectionEntries(['lexical'])\n\n(Showing lines 1-110 of 208. Use offset=111 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Registry ↔ Advisor Routing Drift Guard\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n//\nimport { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { dirname, resolve } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n\nimport { describe, expect, it } from 'vitest';\n\nimport { findAdvisorWorkspaceRoot } from '../lib/utils/workspace-root.js';\nimport {\n  DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL,\n  DEEP_ROUTING_PROJECTION_HASH,\n  SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS,\n} from '../lib/scorer/aliases.js';\n\nconst here = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts","text":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Registry ↔ Advisor Routing Drift Guard\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n//\nimport { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { dirname, resolve } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n\nimport { describe, expect, it } from 'vitest';\n\nimport { findAdvisorWorkspaceRoot } from '../lib/utils/workspace-root.js';\nimport {\n  DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL,\n  DEEP_ROUTING_PROJECTION_HASH,\n  SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS,\n} from '../lib/scorer/aliases.js';\n\nconst here = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\nconst repoRoot = findAdvisorWorkspaceRoot(here);\nconst advisorScript = resolve(\n  repoRoot,\n  '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py',\n);\nconst registryPath = resolve(repoRoot, '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json');\n\ntype RoutingClass = 'lexical' | 'alias-fold' | 'metadata' | 'command-bridge';\n\ninterface AdvisorRouting {\n  readonly routingClass: RoutingClass;\n  readonly legacyAdvisorId?: string;\n  readonly advisorDefaultMode?: boolean;\n  readonly legacyAliases?: readonly string[];\n  readonly packetSkillName: string;\n}\ninterface Mode {\n  readonly workflowMode: string;\n  readonly packet: string;\n  readonly advisorRouting: AdvisorRouting;\n}\ninterface ProjectionEntry {\n  readonly legacyAdvisorId: string;\n  readonly workflowMode: string;\n  readonly routingClass: 'lexical' | 'alias-fold';\n  readonly advisorDefaultMode: boolean;\n  readonly legacyAliases: readonly string[];\n}\ninterface RoutingDump {\n  readonly DEEP_ROUTING_PROJECTION_HASH: string;\n  readonly DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS: string[];\n  readonly DEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY: Record<string, string>;\n  readonly PY_ALIAS_GROUP_KEYS: string[];\n}\nconst registry = JSON.parse(readFileSync(registryPath, 'utf8')) as { modes: readonly Mode[] };\n\nfunction registryProjectionEntries(classes: readonly RoutingClass[]): ProjectionEntry[] {\n  const entries: ProjectionEntry[] = [];\n  for (const mode of registry.modes) {\n    const ar = mode.advisorRouting;\n    if ((ar.routingClass === 'lexical' || ar.routingClass === 'alias-fold') && classes.includes(ar.routingClass)) {\n      entries.push({\n        legacyAdvisorId: ar.legacyAdvisorId as string,\n        workflowMode: mode.workflowMode,\n        routingClass: ar.routingClass,\n        advisorDefaultMode: ar.advisorDefaultMode === true,\n        legacyAliases: [...(ar.legacyAliases ?? [])],\n      });\n    }\n  }\n  return entries.sort((left, right) => left.legacyAdvisorId.localeCompare(right.legacyAdvisorId));\n}\n\nfunction projectionHash(entries: readonly ProjectionEntry[]): string {\n  const canonical = JSON.stringify({\n    skill: 'deep-loop-workflows',\n    entries: entries.map((entry) => ({\n      legacyAdvisorId: entry.legacyAdvisorId,\n      workflowMode: entry.workflowMode,\n      routingClass: entry.routingClass,\n      advisorDefaultMode: entry.advisorDefaultMode,\n      legacyAliases: [...entry.legacyAliases],\n    })),\n  });\n  return `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(canonical).digest('hex')}`;\n}\n\nfunction generatedTypeScriptProjectionEntries(): ProjectionEntry[] {\n  const registryById = new Map(\n    registryProjectionEntries(['lexical', 'alias-fold'])\n      .map((entry) => [entry.legacyAdvisorId, entry] as const),\n  );\n  return Object.entries(DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL)\n    .map(([legacyAdvisorId, workflowMode]) => {\n      const registryEntry = registryById.get(legacyAdvisorId);\n      expect(registryEntry, `registry entry missing for ${legacyAdvisorId}`).toBeDefined();\n      return {\n        legacyAdvisorId,\n        workflowMode,\n        routingClass: registryEntry!.routingClass,\n        advisorDefaultMode: registryEntry!.advisorDefaultMode,\n        legacyAliases: [...(SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS[legacyAdvisorId] ?? [])],\n      };\n    })\n    .sort((left, right) => left.legacyAdvisorId.localeCompare(right.legacyAdvisorId));\n}\n\nfunction generatedPythonProjectionEntries(dump: RoutingDump): ProjectionEntry[] {\n  const registryById = new Map(\n    registryProjectionEntries(['lexical'])","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":110,"totalLines":208,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts","time":{"start":1783487753824,"end":1783487753828}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_034eae1d9ad04063016a4ddd09a8ec819193d0df465280892f"}},"id":"prt_f40276e49001VUr20IUnAQTaoe","sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","messageID":"msg_f402743fe001CeJrohyUww48Fw"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487753909,"sessionID":"ses_0bfdf923effeJgm1s2MxRoJ0VL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_PG1tAsytvdAz1lrbkNtykUmM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs","offset":1,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: 'use strict';\n3: \n4: const crypto = require('node:crypto');\n5: const fs = require('node:fs');\n6: const path = require('node:path');\n7: \n8: const {\n9:   canonicalizeCommand,\n10:   resolveInjectionMode,\n11: } = require('../../deep-loop-workflows/shared/rollout/resolve-injection-mode.cjs');\n12: \n13: const WORKSPACE_ROOT = path.resolve(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', '..');\n14: const MANIFEST_PATH = '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/manifest.jsonl';\n15: \n16: const COMMANDS = {\n17:   'deep/ai-council': {\n18:     slug: 'deep_ai-council',\n19:     legacyBodyPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_ai-council.body.md',\n20:     compiledContractPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_ai-council.contract.md',\n21:   },\n22:   'deep/review': {\n23:     slug: 'deep_review',\n24:     legacyBodyPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_review.body.md',\n25:     compiledContractPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_review.contract.md',\n26:   },\n27:   'deep/research': {\n28:     slug: 'deep_research',\n29:     legacyBodyPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_research.body.md',\n30:     compiledContractPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md',\n31:   },\n32: };\n33: \n34: function absolutePath(sourcePath) {\n35:   return path.resolve(WORKSPACE_ROOT, sourcePath);\n36: }\n37: \n38: function sha256(input) {\n39:   return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(input).digest('hex');\n40: }\n41: \n42: function readBuffer(sourcePath) {\n43:   return fs.readFileSync(absolutePath(sourcePath));\n44: }\n45: \n46: function getCommandDefinition(command) {\n47:   const canonicalCommand = canonicalizeCommand(command);\n48:   const definition = COMMANDS[canonicalCommand];\n49:   if (!definition) {\n50:     const supported = Object.keys(COMMANDS).join(', ');\n51:     throw new Error(`Unsupported command ${command}. Supported commands: ${supported}`);\n52:   }\n53:   return { command: canonicalCommand, ...definition };\n54: }\n55: \n56: function passthroughArgsText(argv) {\n57:   if (argv.length === 0) return '';\n58:   if (argv.length === 1) return argv[0];\n59:   return argv.join(' ');\n60: }\n\n(Showing lines 1-60 of 246. Use offset=61 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n'use strict';\n\nconst crypto = require('node:crypto');\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\nconst {\n  canonicalizeCommand,\n  resolveInjectionMode,\n} = require('../../deep-loop-workflows/shared/rollout/resolve-injection-mode.cjs');\n\nconst WORKSPACE_ROOT = path.resolve(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', '..');\nconst MANIFEST_PATH = '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/manifest.jsonl';\n\nconst COMMANDS = {\n  'deep/ai-council': {\n    slug: 'deep_ai-council',\n    legacyBodyPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_ai-council.body.md',\n    compiledContractPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_ai-council.contract.md',","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n'use strict';\n\nconst crypto = require('node:crypto');\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\nconst {\n  canonicalizeCommand,\n  resolveInjectionMode,\n} = require('../../deep-loop-workflows/shared/rollout/resolve-injection-mode.cjs');\n\nconst WORKSPACE_ROOT = path.resolve(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', '..');\nconst MANIFEST_PATH = '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/manifest.jsonl';\n\nconst COMMANDS = {\n  'deep/ai-council': {\n    slug: 'deep_ai-council',\n    legacyBodyPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_ai-council.body.md',\n    compiledContractPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_ai-council.contract.md',\n  },\n  'deep/review': {\n    slug: 'deep_review',\n    legacyBodyPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_review.body.md',\n    compiledContractPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_review.contract.md',\n  },\n  'deep/research': {\n    slug: 'deep_research',\n    legacyBodyPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep_research.body.md',\n    compiledContractPath: '.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md',\n  },\n};\n\nfunction absolutePath(sourcePath) {\n  return path.resolve(WORKSPACE_ROOT, sourcePath);\n}\n\nfunction sha256(input) {\n  return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(input).digest('hex');\n}\n\nfunction readBuffer(sourcePath) {\n  return fs.readFileSync(absolutePath(sourcePath));\n}\n\nfunction getCommandDefinition(command) {\n  const canonicalCommand = canonicalizeCommand(command);\n  const definition = COMMANDS[canonicalCommand];\n  if (!definition) {\n    const supported = Object.keys(COMMANDS).join(', ');\n    throw new Error(`Unsupported command ${command}. Supported commands: ${supported}`);\n  }\n  return { command: canonicalCommand, ...definition };\n}\n\nfunction passthroughArgsText(argv) {\n  if (argv.length === 0) return '';\n  if (argv.length === 1) return argv[0];\n  return argv.join(' ');\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":60,"totalLines":246,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs","time":{"start":1783487753889,"end":178348775390